{"title_page": "Brandon del Pozo", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Brandon del Pozo\n| office = Chief of Police, Burlington, Vermont\n| predecessor1 = Michael Schirling\n| spouse = Sarah Carnevale (m. 2002)\n| alma_mater = Dartmouth College (AB, 1996), Harvard University (MPA, 2004), John Jay College, CUNY (MA, 2007), The Graduate Center, CUNY (MPhil, 2012 & PhD, 2020)\n| image = \n| smallimage = \n| term_start = September 1, 2015\n| term_end = December 16, 2019\n}}\n\n'''Brandon del Pozo, PhD, MPA, MA''' (born 1974) was the chief of police of [[Burlington, Vermont]]. He was appointed to the position on September 1, 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mychamplainvalley.com/news/brandon-del-pozo-sworn-in-as-burlingtons-new-police-chief|title=Brandon del Pozo Sworn In As Burlington's New Police Chief|last=Leslie|first=Alexandra|date=2015-09-02|language=en-US|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> Prior to coming to Burlington, del Pozo served with the New York City Police Department for nearly two decades, rising to the rank of deputy inspector. While there, he commanded the 6th and 50th Precincts,<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://thevillager.com/villager_426/commander.html|title=Commander's goal is to make Village area 'safe for everyone'|website=thevillager.com|access-date=2016-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130901182243/http://thevillager.com/villager_426/commander.html|archive-date=2013-09-01|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://thevillager.com/villager_423/philosophercommander.html|title='Philosopher commander' at 6th|website=thevillager.com|access-date=2016-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130901182436/http://thevillager.com/villager_423/philosophercommander.html|archive-date=2013-09-01|url-status=dead}}</ref> and served overseas as an intelligence officer for the Arab world and India (based in [[Jordan]]'s capital, [[Amman]]), where he investigated terror attacks to see what lessons they offered for better protecting [[New York City|New York]].<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2008/12/11/fbi-and-nypd-bury-the-hatchet/|title=FBI and NYPD Bury the Hatchet|last=Miller|first=Judith|date=2008-12-11|website=New York Post|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> He has received national recognition for his commitment to innovation and reform.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonvt.gov/Press/Chief-Brandon-del-Pozo-Awarded-National-Innovation-Leadership-Award-by-Top-Progressive|title=Chief Brandon del Pozo Awarded National Innovation & Leadership Award by Top Progressive Policing Organization {{!}} City of Burlington, Vermont|website=burlingtonvt.gov|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nBorn in the [[Bensonhurst, Brooklyn|Bensonhurst]] neighborhood of the [[Borough (New York City)|New York borough]] of [[Brooklyn]] to a Cuban father and Jewish mother,<ref name=\":2\" /> del Pozo graduated from [[Stuyvesant High School]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://westviewnews.org/2012/06/westview-letter-june-2012-beyond-the-letter-of-the-law/|title=WestView Letter June 2012: Beyond the Letter of the Law|date=2012-06-01|language=en-US|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> in New York, then completed a bachelor's degree from [[Dartmouth College]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dartmouthalumnimagazine.com/articles/climb-every-mountain|title=Climb Every Mountain {{!}} Dartmouth Alumni Magazine|website=dartmouthalumnimagazine.com|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref>\n\nDel Pozo earned a master's degree in public administration from the [[John F. Kennedy School of Government]] at [[Harvard University]], and a master of arts in Criminal Justice from [[John Jay College of Criminal Justice|John Jay College]].<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hks.harvard.edu/news-events/publications/hks-magazine/archives/winter-2011/nypd-crimson|title=NYPD Crimson|last=School|first=Harvard Kennedy|website=hks.harvard.edu|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref><ref name=\":12\">{{Cite web|url=http://riverdalepress.com/stories/Del-Pozo-passes-top-cop-torch-at-the-Five-O,48675|title=Del Pozo passes top cop torch at the Five-O|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> While at the Kennedy School, he was a 9/11 Public Service Fellow, in recognition of the sacrifices made by first responders on [[9/11|that day]].<ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mychamplainvalley.com/news/btv-police-chief-reflects-on-911-experience-as-nypd-officer|title=BTV Police Chief Reflects On 9/11 Experience As NYPD Officer|last=DaSilva|first=Staci|date=2015-09-11|language=en-US|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref>\n\nHe holds a PhD in Philosophy and the enroute MPhil degree from [[City University of New York Graduate Center|The Graduate School and University Center of the City University of New York]]. His dissertation, \"The Police and the State,\" \"offers a systematic account of the relationship between the police and the democratic state\" in terms of contemporary political philosophy.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=del Pozo|first=Brandon|date=2020-02-01|title=The Police and the State|url=https://academicworks.cuny.edu/gc_etds/3557|journal=All Dissertations, Theses, and Capstone Projects}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nCiting the challenges of policing in the United States,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/10/nyregion/in-week-of-emotional-swings-police-face-a-dual-role-villain-and-victim.html|title=In Week of Emotional Swings, Police Face a Dual Role: Villain and Victim|last=Wilson|first=Michael|date=2016-07-09|last2=Schwirtz|first2=Michael|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> del Pozo came to Burlington with a desire to improve police services in the city as a model for progress in the profession.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sevendaysvt.com/vermont/scholar-in-chief-burlingtons-top-cop-del-pozo-aims-to-rewrite-policing/Content?oid=3476938|title=Burlington's Top Cop, Brandon del Pozo, Aims to Rewrite Policing|last=Freese|first=Alicia|website=Seven Days|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> His appointment was contested by some locals due to his prior work with the [[New York City Police Department|New York Police Department]] (NYPD).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sevendaysvt.com/vermont/burlington-city-councilors-stand-by-their-man-del-pozo-is-new-police-chief/Content?oid=2740755|title=Burlington City Councilors Stand By Their Man: Del Pozo Is New Police Chief|last=Hallenbeck|first=Terri|website=Seven Days|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> After a public discussion of his views, his nomination was unanimously approved by the Burlington City Council.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2015/07/13/burlington-council-backs-del-pozo-for-police-chief|title=Burlington City Council Backs del Pozo for Police Chief|last=Hallenbeck|first=Terri|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref>\n\n=== Opioid Addiction and Overdose Reduction ===\nOpioid abuse and dependency have been a concern for the city and its police in light of the state of Vermont's wider struggles with opioid addiction.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/news/the-new-face-of-heroin-20140403|title=The New Face of Heroin|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/vermont/death-by-drugs-opiates-claimed-a-record-number-of-vermonters-in-2016/Content?oid=3983873|title=Death by Drugs: Opiates Claimed a Record Number of Vermonters in 2016|last=Davis|first=Mark|website=Seven Days|language=en|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> Burlington mayor [[Miro Weinberger]] directed del Pozo to create and implement a strategy<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2016/01/12/del-pozos-diagnosis-police-chief-outlines-opiate-strategy|title=Del Pozo's Diagnosis: Police Chief Outlines Opiate Strategy|last=Freese|first=Alicia|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> for addressing its effects that focuses on public health rather than law enforcement<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://digital.vpr.net/post/one-year-burlingtons-police-chief-reflects-use-force-and-opiate-addiction|title=One Year In, Burlington's Police Chief Reflects On Use Of Force And Opiate Addiction|last=Connors|first=Mitch Wertlieb, Liam|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> and uses data and collaboration as cornerstones of the approach.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2016/04/25/help-wanted-two-good-people-to-assist-burlington-in-addressing-the-opiate-problem|title=Help Wanted: Two Good People To Assist Burlington in Addressing the Opiate Problem|last=Freese|first=Alicia|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> Shortly after taking on the leadership of the Burlington Police Department, del Pozo began a wide-ranging initiative.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vera.org/the-human-toll-of-jail/david-and-goliath|title=David and Goliath|last=Hyperakt|date=2018-06-08|website=Vera|language=en|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> He directed all patrol officers to carry Naloxone, the overdose reversal drug,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonvt.gov/sites/default/files/police/press/1-8-16,%20press%20release%20-%20Naloxone.pdf|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170128153232/https://www.burlingtonvt.gov/sites/default/files/police/press/1-8-16,%20press%20release%20-%20Naloxone.pdf|archive-date=2017-01-28|url-status=dead}}</ref> and assisted the mayor's office with the creation of the city's Opioid Policy Coordinator position, as well as staffing his office with analyst with graduate training in epidemiology and biostatistics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/OneNorthAvenue/status/966683496382115841?s=19|title=So pleased to welcome Kayla Donohue to our CommunityStat team! She's our opioid data analyst. Trained in epidemiology & biostatistics at Boston University, she'll work with our @OpioidPolicyBTV coordinator to ensure policing & public health never part ways in #BTV.pic.twitter.com/F8mNJGXKOB|last=Police|first=Burlington|date=2018-02-22|website=@OneNorthAvenue|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> Based out of the police department, the two positions vet police work for better public health outcomes and assist the city in formulating policies, directives and public engagements to reduce the morbidity and mortality associated with opioid abuse.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/2016/11/15/burlington-opioid-policy-leader-pioneers-data-based-approach/93649662/|title=BTV's opioid-policy leader pioneers data-based approach|newspaper=Burlington Free Press|access-date=2016-11-28}}</ref>\n\nDel Pozo has been known to personally meet with and try to help members of the community suffering from addiction,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/12/nyregion/when-opioid-addicts-find-an-ally-in-blue.html|title=When Opioid Addicts Find an Ally in Blue|last=Baker|first=Al|date=2017-06-12|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-07-13|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> and his insights into the need for swift action and an end to stigma in treating addiction and overdose have gone viral and gained national attention.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wamu.org/story/18/10/26/viral-opioid-obituary-and-police-chiefs-response-show-journey-of-addiction-resilience/|title=Viral Opioid Obituary \u2014 And Police Chief's Response \u2014 Show Journey Of Addiction, Resilience|website=WAMU|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> He has been vocal about the need for all people suffering from opioid addiction to have prompt access to the medications proven to treat it,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tonic.vice.com/en_us/article/wjbabn/buprenorphine-on-demand|title=These Cities Are Finally Making Addiction Meds Easier to Get|last=Szalavitz|first=Maia|last2=Rinkunas|first2=Susan|date=2018-06-26|website=Tonic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> including prisoners,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/politics/government/2017/04/12/burlington-police-chief-asks-more-drug-treatment-prison/100189662/|title=Chief: More drug treatment needed in prison|website=Burlington Free Press|language=en|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> and he adopted a policy in conjunction with the county prosecutor where his department would not arrest people for unprescribed possession of [[buprenorphine]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/vermont/burlington-to-ease-access-to-opioid-addiction-medication/Content?oid=16884183|title=Burlington to Ease Access to Opioid Addiction Medication|last=Freese|first=Alicia|website=Seven Days|language=en|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/wjbabn/buprenorphine-on-demand|title=These Cities Are Finally Making Addiction Meds Easier to Get|last=Szalavitz|first=Maia|date=2018-06-26|website=Vice|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> In early 2020, the city of Philadelphia took the same position towards buprenorphine, citing Burlington's leadership on the issue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/DA_LarryKrasner/status/1222312417914490882|title=Grateful to you all for leading the way.|last=Krasner|first=DA Larry|date=2020-01-28|website=@DA_LarryKrasner|language=en|access-date=2020-01-29}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, as the rest of Vermont saw a 20% increase in opioid overdose deaths, Burlington's county saw a 50% decline in these deaths, to their lowest levels since 2013, when the state began keeping records.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2019/02/14/opioid-deaths-rise-in-vermont-but-plummet-in-chittenden-county|title=Opioid Deaths Rise in Vermont but Plummet in Chittenden County|last=Jickling|first=Katie|website=Seven Days|language=en|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> In 2019, Burlington's county saw a further 12% reduction in overdose deaths, resulting in a 60% reduction in overdose fatalities in the city since their peak in 2017, when del Pozo and the mayor began to coordinate the community's response to the crisis.\n\nDel Pozo serves on the board of trustees of the [[Howard Center]], Vermont's largest addiction and mental health service provider.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vermontbiz.com/news/2019/january/08/connolly-del-pozo-couture-willenborg-join-howard-center-board|title=Connolly, del Pozo, Couture, Willenborg join Howard Center board|date=2019-01-08|website=Vermont Business Magazine|language=en|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref>\n\n=== Use of Force Reform ===\nIn the winter of 2016, after a Burlington police officer killed Phil Grenon, a man who attacked the police with knives at the end of a prolonged standoff,<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/2016/05/11/burlington-police-shooting-videos-online/84236444/|title=Burlington police post shooting videos online|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> del Pozo began a program to improve outcomes in the use of force, piloting the [[Police Executive Research Forum]]'s (PERF) new force guidelines and curriculum<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/local/2016/09/15/burlington-police-training-deescalation/90357496/|title=BPD training teaches peaceful deescalation|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref><ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mychamplainvalley.com/news/btv-police-undergo-de-escalation-crisis-training|title=BTV Police Undergo De-Escalation Crisis Training|last=Aragon|first=Rachel|date=2016-09-14|language=en-US|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> and introducing new tactics and technologies that avert physical confrontations.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/2016/09/28/burlington-police-department-adds-two-scout-robots/91210684/|title=Burlington Police Department adds two scout robots|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> The Reveal, a show syndicated by American Public Media, produced a segment taking a close look at the incident and its aftermath: \"When Tasers Fail.\"<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.revealnews.org/episodes/when-tasers-fail/|title=When Tasers fail|date=2019-05-11|website=Reveal|language=en|access-date=2019-09-25}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, del Pozo gave the highest award in the department to an officer who was in the path of a robbery suspect fleeing in a vehicle and would have been justified in opening fire on the vehicle, but chose not to,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/BrandondelPozo/status/974016384186376192|title=Last May, Corporal Mike Hemond, gun drawn on a crowded street, faced a robbery suspect bearing down on him in a car. He could've shot, but didn't. The suspect was later arrested. Today, I gave CPL Hemond the Chief's Award for this & other acts of courage. http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/local/2017/05/23/chief-body-cam-video-shows-officers-bravery-and-restraint/339361001/\u00a0\u2026pic.twitter.com/4zDKEUCDa5|last=Pozo|first=Brandon del|date=2018-03-14|website=@BrandondelPozo|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> saying that restraint was a valuable quality in a police officer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/local/2017/05/23/chief-body-cam-video-shows-officers-bravery-and-restraint/339361001/|title=Chief: Body cam video shows officer's restraint|last=Murray|first=Elizabeth|website=Burlington Free Press|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> He also investigated the Vermont State Police Academy for allegations that officers were needlessly being struck unexpectedly in the head during training scenarios, causing a pattern of concussions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vtdigger.org/2019/01/07/recruits-suffer-concussions-hitchhiker-scenario-police-academy-drill/|title=Recruits suffer concussions during 'Hitchhiker Scenario' police academy drill|date=2019-01-07|website=VTDigger|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> As a result, the academy settled a suit with one of the injured students and ceased delivering unexpected blows to the heads of its recruits.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vtdigger.org/2019/10/09/burlington-officer-settles-with-police-academy-for-30000-in-hitchhiker-scenario-suit/|title=Police academy settles for $30,000 in 'hitchhiker scenario' suit|last=Oct 9 2019October 10|first=Ellie French|last2=Footnote|first2=2019 {{!}} One Reader|date=2019-10-09|website=VTDigger|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2019, del Pozo authored an op-ed in ''[[The New York Times]]'' arguing that when confronting persons in crisis armed with knives, police officers should view their firearms as a means to defend themselves and others from harm, rather than the means by which to persuade the person to drop the knife, often accompanied by yelling orders that only escalate the person in crisis.<ref name=\":11\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/13/opinion/police-shootings-guns.html|title=Opinion {{!}} I'm a Police Chief. We Need to Change How Officers View Their Guns.|last=Pozo|first=Brandon del|date=2019-11-13|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-01-17|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Instead, he advocated that officers should have a gun at the ready, but engage with distressed suspects as if the officer was unarmed and had to rely on deescalation and persuasion instead.<ref name=\":11\" /> \n\nA few weeks later, his view was echoed by the Washington Post editorial board, which observed that the present protocol \"is for officers to advance and draw their guns, repeatedly shout 'Drop the knife!' and hope for compliance. But pointing a gun at a person in crisis tends to increase their anxiety and exacerbate the situation, while advancing toward them may put the officer in unnecessary danger.\" The Post repeated del Pozo's observation that, in sum, \"officers should be trained not to point weapons at potentially suicidal people, to move a safe distance away and continue backing away when possible, and to converse with the person rather than shouting commands.\" <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/suicide-by-cop-is-a-persistent-problem-heres-how-to-prevent-it/2020/01/10/dc1a1358-324d-11ea-a053-dc6d944ba776_story.html|title='Suicide by cop' is a persistent problem. Here's how to prevent it|last=The Editorial Board|date=10 January 2020|website=Washington Post|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Both opinion pieces were based on a research report by PERF outlining the potential for such innovations in police tactics to prevent shootings and save lives.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.policeforum.org/suicidebycop|title=Suicide By Cop|website=policeforum.org|access-date=2020-01-18}}</ref>\n\n=== Transparency ===\nAn advocate for greater transparency in policing and government, del Pozo created a police data transparency portal where he discloses a range of raw and processed data about the work of the Burlington Police under a quote by legal philosopher [[Jeremy Waldron]]: \"In a democracy, the accountable agents of the people owe the people an account of what they have been doing, and a refusal to provide this is simple insolence.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonvt.gov/Police/Data|title=BPD Crime Data {{!}} City of Burlington, Vermont|website=burlingtonvt.gov|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref>  He has spoken at the Obama [[White House]] to an audience of police leaders on the value of the practice as part of efforts to implement the recommendations of the President's Task Force on 21st Century Policing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wcax.com/story/32807370/police-chief-del-pozo-reflects-on-trip-to-washington-dc|title=Police Chief Del Pozo reflects on trip to Washington D.C.|last=McGilvery|first=Keith|access-date=2016-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160926072555/http://www.wcax.com/story/32807370/police-chief-del-pozo-reflects-on-trip-to-washington-dc|archive-date=2016-09-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> During his tenure, the police department has made concerted efforts to diversify its rank and file, with moderate success.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/opinion/editorials/2017/01/08/editorial-burlington-polices-diversity-move/96265960/|title=Editorial: Burlington police does diversity|newspaper=Burlington Free Press|access-date=2017-01-10}}</ref>\n\n=== Overseas Intelligence ===\nIn 2005, citing intelligence failures that led to the [[September 11 attacks|9/11 terror attacks]], the NYPD selected del Pozo to create and staff its first intelligence liaison post with the Arab world, based out of Amman, Jordan.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Dickey|first=Christopher|title=Securing the City: Inside America's Best Counterterror Force--The NYPD|publisher=Simon & Schuster|year=2009|isbn=|location=New York|pages=147}}</ref> Embedded with the Jordanian National Police, he responded to [[2005 Amman bombings|suicide bombings at Jordanian hotels]] planned and executed by [[Abu Musab al-Zarqawi]], and an attack on a Roman amphitheater.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Butcher|first=Tim|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/1528110/Terror-in-the-amphitheatre-as-tourists-are-shot.html|title=Terror in the amphitheatre as tourists are shot|journal=Daily Telegraph|date=2006-09-04|access-date=2020-02-12|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref> He also responded to two attacks in Mumbai, India: [[2006 Mumbai train bombings|a 2006 bombing of seven trains]] on the city's commuter rail,<ref>{{Cite book|last=Comiskey|first=John|title=EFFECTIVE STATE, LOCAL, AND TRIBAL POLICE INTELLIGENCE: THE NEW YORK CITY POLICE DEPARTMENT'S INTELLIGENCE ENTERPRISE|publisher=The US Naval Postgraduate School|year=2010|isbn=|location=Monterey, CA|pages=71}}</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/Mumbai-terror-makes-NYPD-Blue/articleshow/1785453.cms</ref> and the [[2008 Mumbai attacks|2008 Lashkar-e-Taiba-led attack on downtown Mumbai]] itself, where a team of gunmen attacked hotels, transportation hubs, tourist areas and a Jewish cultural center. Del Pozo reported his analyses back to the NYPD and other agencies,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=97912059|title=Mumbai Attacks Offer Clues To Security|website=NPR.org|language=en|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref> assessing how these attacks could be replicated by exploiting security vulnerabilities in New York City,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wnyc.org/story/75838-how-safe-are-hotels-and-other-urban-spaces/|title=How Safe Are Hotels and Other Urban Spaces? {{!}} WNYC {{!}} New York Public Radio, Podcasts, Live Streaming Radio, News|website=WNYC|language=en|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref> and what measures could be taken to prevent them.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.utep.edu/clhb/_Files/docs/DHS_Research_in_Brief_Dahl.pdf|title=Counterterrorism and Intelligence|last=|first=|date=|website=Center for Law and Human Behavior, UT el Paso|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> His role was unique in that there was no other US intelligence officer conducting work on behalf of a municipal police department in either region.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Dahl|first=Erik J.|date=2014-07-03|title=Local approaches to counterterrorism: the New York Police Department model|journal=Journal of Policing, Intelligence and Counter Terrorism|volume=9|issue=2|pages=81\u201397|doi=10.1080/18335330.2014.940815|issn=1833-5330}}</ref>\n\n=== Recognition ===\nIn May 2016, the PERF awarded del Pozo its Gary Hayes Memorial Award for his innovation and leadership.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.policeforum.org/assets/docs/Subject_to_Debate/Debate2016/debate_2016_mayjun.pdf|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> ''[[The New York Times|New York Times]]'' editor and book critic [[Dwight Garner (critic)|Dwight Garner]] characterized del Pozo as \"thoughtful and sane.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/dwightgarner/status/752494957835984896|title=Dwight Garner on Twitter|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref>\n\nHe is presently writing a book about police work for [[Farrar, Straus and Giroux|Farrar, Straus & Giroux]].<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Resignation ==\nDel Pozo resigned as police chief on December 16, 2019, after disclosing that he had used an anonymous Twitter account (\"WinkleWatchers\") to direct approximately eight tweets at a critic of the city leadership, for approximately an hour on July 4, before deleting the tweets and the account within the hour.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/2019/12/16/burlington-police-chief-brandon-del-pozo-faces-call-resign-vermont/2662672001/|title=Burlington Police Chief del Pozo resigns: Here's how he got to that point|last=Murray|first=Elizabeth|website=Burlington Free Press|language=en|access-date=2019-12-17}}</ref> When asked by a reporter about the tweets later that July, del Pozo repeatedly denied authorship.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2019/12/12/burlington-police-chief-admits-he-used-an-anonymous-twitter-account-to-taunt-a-critic|title=Burlington Police Chief Admits He Used an Anonymous Twitter Account to Taunt a Critic|last=Lamdin|first=Courtney|website=Seven Days|language=en|access-date=2019-12-17}}</ref> Five months later, when Del Pozo admitted that he authored the tweets, he resigned. In a statement to The New York Times, he said he wrote eight Tweets \u201cin 45 minutes of my life that I wish I could take back, but they taught me that nothing good ever comes from letting social media criticism get under your skin... It was a real lesson learned during a stressful time in my life.\u201d<ref>{{Cite news|last=Cramer|first=Maria|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/11/us/burlington-police-jan-wright-twitter.html|title=Yet Another Vermont Police Chief Quits Over Fake Social Media Accounts|date=2020-02-11|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-02-12|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> \n\nAccording to ''Seven Days'', an attorney suing the city complained that del Pozo didn't list the Twitter account in court filings pertaining to an unrelated use of force lawsuit.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2019/12/13/on-tape-burlington-police-chief-lied-repeatedly-about-twitter-account-in-july-call|title=On Tape, Burlington Police Chief Repeatedly Lied About Twitter Account in July|website=Seven Days|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> The federal court judge reviewing the complaint dismissed it, ruling that the attorney violated good faith by making the complaint,<ref>https://vtdigger.org/2020/01/24/federal-judge-denies-motion-to-sanction-burlington-over-ex-chiefs-twitter-account/</ref> and finding \"no evidence that the omissions had caused any 'discernable [sic] harm.'\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2020/01/22/judge-wont-sanction-burlington-over-anonymous-twitter-account|title=Judge Won't Sanction Burlington Over Anonymous Twitter Account|website=Seven Days}}</ref>\n\nIn his resignation letter, del Pozo stated he would soon complete is doctorate in political philosophy, which he did a month later. He also voiced aspirations to complete his book for [[Farrar, Straus and Giroux|Farrar, Straus & Giroux]], and help establish a research center on policing and public health.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vermontbiz.com/news/2019/december/16/burlington-police-chief-del-pozo-resigns|title=Burlington Police Chief del Pozo resigns|date=2019-12-16|website=Vermont Business Magazine|language=en|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nDel Pozo married Sarah Carnevale in 2002.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/03/style/weddings-vows-sarah-carnevale-and-brandon-del-pozo.html|title=WEDDINGS: VOWS; Sarah Carnevale and Brandon del Pozo|last=Ellin|first=Abby|date=2002-03-03|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> They moved to Burlington from the village of [[Cold Spring, New York]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://highlandscurrent.com/2015/08/01/the-paper-interviews-brandon-del-pozo/|title=The Paper Interviews: Brandon del Pozo|last=Turton|first=Michael|website=Highlands Current|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> He wrote and directed a narrative short film, ''Sunday 1287'',<ref>{{Citation|title=Sunday 1287|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5232374/|accessdate=2017-07-13}}</ref> which screened at the Middlebury and Vermont International Film Festivals.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mynbc5.com/article/burlington-police-chief-directs-film-to-play-in-vermont-international-film-festival/7022442|title=Burlington Police Chief directs film to play in Vermont International Film Festival|last=Isaacs|first=Abby|date=2016-10-21|newspaper=WPTZ|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref> The film was based on a crime he investigated while commanding a precinct in the New York borough of [[the Bronx]]. In 2018, he suffered multiple serious injuries in a bicycle accident, was evacuated to an intensive care unit by helicopter, and went on to recover and return to full duty in his role.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vtdigger.org/2018/08/12/thousands-athletes-done/|title=I was doing what thousands of athletes have done|last=Aug 12 2018August 13|first=Mark Johnson|last2=Footnotes|first2=2018 {{!}} No Reader|date=2018-08-12|website=VTDigger|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> An outdoors enthusiast,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://rootsrated.com/stories/burlingtons-new-police-chief|title=Burlington's New Police Chief is a Badass|date=2016-05-17|newspaper=RootsRated|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref> he has climbed New Hampshire's [[Four-thousand footers|48 highest mountains]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dartmouthalumnimagazine.com/articles/climb-every-mountain|title=Climb Every Mountain|last=Brandon del Pozo \u201996 {{!}} Jan - Feb 2016|website=Dartmouth Alumni Magazine|language=en|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref> completed the Lake Placid Half Ironman and other triathlons, and written for publications about cycling and climbing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.adirondacklifemag.com/blogs/2016/05/23/cycle-adirondacks/|title=Adirondack Life Blog Archive Cycle Adirondacks - Adirondack Life|website=adirondacklifemag.com|access-date=2016-11-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.adirondacklifemag.com/blogs/2017/04/06/the-ice-man/|title=Adirondack Life Article - The Ice Man - Adirondack Life|website=adirondacklifemag.com|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Del Pozo, Brandon}}\n[[Category:John F. Kennedy School of Government alumni]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:American municipal police chiefs]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Bensonhurst, Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:Dartmouth College alumni]]\n[[Category:Stuyvesant High School alumni]]\n[[Category:John Jay College of Criminal Justice alumni]]\n[[Category:Graduate Center, CUNY alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Brandon del Pozo\n| office = Chief of Police, Burlington, Vermont\n| predecessor1 = Michael Schirling\n| spouse = Sarah Carnevale (m. 2002)\n| alma_mater = Dartmouth College (AB, 1996), Harvard University (MPA, 2004), John Jay College, CUNY (MA, 2007), The Graduate Center, CUNY (MPhil, 2012 & PhD, 2020)\n| image = \n| smallimage = \n| term_start = September 1, 2015\n| term_end = December 16, 2019\n}}\n\n'''Brandon del Pozo, PhD, MPA, MA''' (born 1974) was the chief of police of [[Burlington, Vermont]]. He was appointed to the position on September 1, 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mychamplainvalley.com/news/brandon-del-pozo-sworn-in-as-burlingtons-new-police-chief|title=Brandon del Pozo Sworn In As Burlington's New Police Chief|last=Leslie|first=Alexandra|date=2015-09-02|language=en-US|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> Prior to coming to Burlington, del Pozo served with the New York City Police Department for nearly two decades, rising to the rank of deputy inspector. While there, he commanded the 6th and 50th Precincts,<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://thevillager.com/villager_426/commander.html|title=Commander's goal is to make Village area 'safe for everyone'|website=thevillager.com|access-date=2016-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130901182243/http://thevillager.com/villager_426/commander.html|archive-date=2013-09-01|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://thevillager.com/villager_423/philosophercommander.html|title='Philosopher commander' at 6th|website=thevillager.com|access-date=2016-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130901182436/http://thevillager.com/villager_423/philosophercommander.html|archive-date=2013-09-01|url-status=dead}}</ref> and served overseas as an intelligence officer for the Arab world and India (based in [[Jordan]]'s capital, [[Amman]]), where he investigated terror attacks to see what lessons they offered for better protecting [[New York City|New York]].<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2008/12/11/fbi-and-nypd-bury-the-hatchet/|title=FBI and NYPD Bury the Hatchet|last=Miller|first=Judith|date=2008-12-11|website=New York Post|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> He has received national recognition for his commitment to innovation and reform.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonvt.gov/Press/Chief-Brandon-del-Pozo-Awarded-National-Innovation-Leadership-Award-by-Top-Progressive|title=Chief Brandon del Pozo Awarded National Innovation & Leadership Award by Top Progressive Policing Organization {{!}} City of Burlington, Vermont|website=burlingtonvt.gov|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nBorn in the [[Bensonhurst, Brooklyn|Bensonhurst]] neighborhood of the [[Borough (New York City)|New York borough]] of [[Brooklyn]] to a Cuban father and Jewish mother,<ref name=\":2\" /> del Pozo graduated from [[Stuyvesant High School]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://westviewnews.org/2012/06/westview-letter-june-2012-beyond-the-letter-of-the-law/|title=WestView Letter June 2012: Beyond the Letter of the Law|date=2012-06-01|language=en-US|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> in New York, then completed a bachelor's degree from [[Dartmouth College]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dartmouthalumnimagazine.com/articles/climb-every-mountain|title=Climb Every Mountain {{!}} Dartmouth Alumni Magazine|website=dartmouthalumnimagazine.com|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref>\n\nDel Pozo earned a master's degree in public administration from the [[John F. Kennedy School of Government]] at [[Harvard University]], and a master of arts in Criminal Justice from [[John Jay College of Criminal Justice|John Jay College]].<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hks.harvard.edu/news-events/publications/hks-magazine/archives/winter-2011/nypd-crimson|title=NYPD Crimson|last=School|first=Harvard Kennedy|website=hks.harvard.edu|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref><ref name=\":12\">{{Cite web|url=http://riverdalepress.com/stories/Del-Pozo-passes-top-cop-torch-at-the-Five-O,48675|title=Del Pozo passes top cop torch at the Five-O|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> While at the Kennedy School, he was a 9/11 Public Service Fellow, in recognition of the sacrifices made by first responders on [[9/11|that day]].<ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mychamplainvalley.com/news/btv-police-chief-reflects-on-911-experience-as-nypd-officer|title=BTV Police Chief Reflects On 9/11 Experience As NYPD Officer|last=DaSilva|first=Staci|date=2015-09-11|language=en-US|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref>\n\nHe holds a PhD in Philosophy and the enroute MPhil degree from [[City University of New York Graduate Center|The Graduate School and University Center of the City University of New York]]. His dissertation, \"The Police and the State,\" \"offers a systematic account of the relationship between the police and the democratic state\" in terms of contemporary political philosophy.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=del Pozo|first=Brandon|date=2020-02-01|title=The Police and the State|url=https://academicworks.cuny.edu/gc_etds/3557|journal=All Dissertations, Theses, and Capstone Projects}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nCiting the challenges of policing in the United States,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/10/nyregion/in-week-of-emotional-swings-police-face-a-dual-role-villain-and-victim.html|title=In Week of Emotional Swings, Police Face a Dual Role: Villain and Victim|last=Wilson|first=Michael|date=2016-07-09|last2=Schwirtz|first2=Michael|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> del Pozo came to Burlington with a desire to improve police services in the city as a model for progress in the profession.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sevendaysvt.com/vermont/scholar-in-chief-burlingtons-top-cop-del-pozo-aims-to-rewrite-policing/Content?oid=3476938|title=Burlington's Top Cop, Brandon del Pozo, Aims to Rewrite Policing|last=Freese|first=Alicia|website=Seven Days|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> His appointment was contested by some locals due to his prior work with the [[New York City Police Department|New York Police Department]] (NYPD).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sevendaysvt.com/vermont/burlington-city-councilors-stand-by-their-man-del-pozo-is-new-police-chief/Content?oid=2740755|title=Burlington City Councilors Stand By Their Man: Del Pozo Is New Police Chief|last=Hallenbeck|first=Terri|website=Seven Days|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> After a public discussion of his views, his nomination was unanimously approved by the Burlington City Council.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2015/07/13/burlington-council-backs-del-pozo-for-police-chief|title=Burlington City Council Backs del Pozo for Police Chief|last=Hallenbeck|first=Terri|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref>\n\n=== Opioid Addiction and Overdose Reduction ===\nOpioid abuse and dependency have been a concern for the city and its police in light of the state of Vermont's wider struggles with opioid addiction.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/news/the-new-face-of-heroin-20140403|title=The New Face of Heroin|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/vermont/death-by-drugs-opiates-claimed-a-record-number-of-vermonters-in-2016/Content?oid=3983873|title=Death by Drugs: Opiates Claimed a Record Number of Vermonters in 2016|last=Davis|first=Mark|website=Seven Days|language=en|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> Burlington mayor [[Miro Weinberger]] directed del Pozo to create and implement a strategy<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2016/01/12/del-pozos-diagnosis-police-chief-outlines-opiate-strategy|title=Del Pozo's Diagnosis: Police Chief Outlines Opiate Strategy|last=Freese|first=Alicia|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> for addressing its effects that focuses on public health rather than law enforcement<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://digital.vpr.net/post/one-year-burlingtons-police-chief-reflects-use-force-and-opiate-addiction|title=One Year In, Burlington's Police Chief Reflects On Use Of Force And Opiate Addiction|last=Connors|first=Mitch Wertlieb, Liam|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> and uses data and collaboration as cornerstones of the approach.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2016/04/25/help-wanted-two-good-people-to-assist-burlington-in-addressing-the-opiate-problem|title=Help Wanted: Two Good People To Assist Burlington in Addressing the Opiate Problem|last=Freese|first=Alicia|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> Shortly after taking on the leadership of the Burlington Police Department, del Pozo began a wide-ranging initiative.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vera.org/the-human-toll-of-jail/david-and-goliath|title=David and Goliath|last=Hyperakt|date=2018-06-08|website=Vera|language=en|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> He directed all patrol officers to carry Naloxone, the overdose reversal drug,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonvt.gov/sites/default/files/police/press/1-8-16,%20press%20release%20-%20Naloxone.pdf|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170128153232/https://www.burlingtonvt.gov/sites/default/files/police/press/1-8-16,%20press%20release%20-%20Naloxone.pdf|archive-date=2017-01-28|url-status=dead}}</ref> and assisted the mayor's office with the creation of the city's Opioid Policy Coordinator position, as well as staffing his office with analyst with graduate training in epidemiology and biostatistics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/OneNorthAvenue/status/966683496382115841?s=19|title=So pleased to welcome Kayla Donohue to our CommunityStat team! She's our opioid data analyst. Trained in epidemiology & biostatistics at Boston University, she'll work with our @OpioidPolicyBTV coordinator to ensure policing & public health never part ways in #BTV.pic.twitter.com/F8mNJGXKOB|last=Police|first=Burlington|date=2018-02-22|website=@OneNorthAvenue|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> Based out of the police department, the two positions vet police work for better public health outcomes and assist the city in formulating policies, directives and public engagements to reduce the morbidity and mortality associated with opioid abuse.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/2016/11/15/burlington-opioid-policy-leader-pioneers-data-based-approach/93649662/|title=BTV's opioid-policy leader pioneers data-based approach|newspaper=Burlington Free Press|access-date=2016-11-28}}</ref>\n\nDel Pozo has been known to personally meet with and try to help members of the community suffering from addiction,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/12/nyregion/when-opioid-addicts-find-an-ally-in-blue.html|title=When Opioid Addicts Find an Ally in Blue|last=Baker|first=Al|date=2017-06-12|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-07-13|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> and his insights into the need for swift action and an end to stigma in treating addiction and overdose have gone viral and gained national attention.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wamu.org/story/18/10/26/viral-opioid-obituary-and-police-chiefs-response-show-journey-of-addiction-resilience/|title=Viral Opioid Obituary \u2014 And Police Chief's Response \u2014 Show Journey Of Addiction, Resilience|website=WAMU|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> He has been vocal about the need for all people suffering from opioid addiction to have prompt access to the medications proven to treat it,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tonic.vice.com/en_us/article/wjbabn/buprenorphine-on-demand|title=These Cities Are Finally Making Addiction Meds Easier to Get|last=Szalavitz|first=Maia|last2=Rinkunas|first2=Susan|date=2018-06-26|website=Tonic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> including prisoners,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/politics/government/2017/04/12/burlington-police-chief-asks-more-drug-treatment-prison/100189662/|title=Chief: More drug treatment needed in prison|website=Burlington Free Press|language=en|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> and he adopted a policy in conjunction with the county prosecutor where his department would not arrest people for unprescribed possession of [[buprenorphine]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/vermont/burlington-to-ease-access-to-opioid-addiction-medication/Content?oid=16884183|title=Burlington to Ease Access to Opioid Addiction Medication|last=Freese|first=Alicia|website=Seven Days|language=en|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/wjbabn/buprenorphine-on-demand|title=These Cities Are Finally Making Addiction Meds Easier to Get|last=Szalavitz|first=Maia|date=2018-06-26|website=Vice|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> In early 2020, the city of Philadelphia took the same position towards buprenorphine, citing Burlington's leadership on the issue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/DA_LarryKrasner/status/1222312417914490882|title=Grateful to you all for leading the way.|last=Krasner|first=DA Larry|date=2020-01-28|website=@DA_LarryKrasner|language=en|access-date=2020-01-29}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, as the rest of Vermont saw a 20% increase in opioid overdose deaths, Burlington's county saw a 50% decline in these deaths, to their lowest levels since 2013, when the state began keeping records.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2019/02/14/opioid-deaths-rise-in-vermont-but-plummet-in-chittenden-county|title=Opioid Deaths Rise in Vermont but Plummet in Chittenden County|last=Jickling|first=Katie|website=Seven Days|language=en|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> In 2019, Burlington's county saw a further 12% reduction in overdose deaths, resulting in a 60% reduction in overdose fatalities in the city since their peak in 2017, when del Pozo and the mayor began to coordinate the community's response to the crisis.\n\nDel Pozo serves on the board of trustees of the [[Howard Center]], Vermont's largest addiction and mental health service provider.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vermontbiz.com/news/2019/january/08/connolly-del-pozo-couture-willenborg-join-howard-center-board|title=Connolly, del Pozo, Couture, Willenborg join Howard Center board|date=2019-01-08|website=Vermont Business Magazine|language=en|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref>\n\n=== Use of Force Reform ===\nIn the winter of 2016, after a Burlington police officer killed Phil Grenon, a man who attacked the police with knives at the end of a prolonged standoff,<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/2016/05/11/burlington-police-shooting-videos-online/84236444/|title=Burlington police post shooting videos online|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> del Pozo began a program to improve outcomes in the use of force, piloting the [[Police Executive Research Forum]]'s (PERF) new force guidelines and curriculum<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/local/2016/09/15/burlington-police-training-deescalation/90357496/|title=BPD training teaches peaceful deescalation|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref><ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mychamplainvalley.com/news/btv-police-undergo-de-escalation-crisis-training|title=BTV Police Undergo De-Escalation Crisis Training|last=Aragon|first=Rachel|date=2016-09-14|language=en-US|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> and introducing new tactics and technologies that avert physical confrontations.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/2016/09/28/burlington-police-department-adds-two-scout-robots/91210684/|title=Burlington Police Department adds two scout robots|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> The Reveal, a show syndicated by American Public Media, produced a segment taking a close look at the incident and its aftermath: \"When Tasers Fail.\"<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.revealnews.org/episodes/when-tasers-fail/|title=When Tasers fail|date=2019-05-11|website=Reveal|language=en|access-date=2019-09-25}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, del Pozo gave the highest award in the department to an officer who was in the path of a robbery suspect fleeing in a vehicle and would have been justified in opening fire on the vehicle, but chose not to,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/BrandondelPozo/status/974016384186376192|title=Last May, Corporal Mike Hemond, gun drawn on a crowded street, faced a robbery suspect bearing down on him in a car. He could've shot, but didn't. The suspect was later arrested. Today, I gave CPL Hemond the Chief's Award for this & other acts of courage. http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/local/2017/05/23/chief-body-cam-video-shows-officers-bravery-and-restraint/339361001/\u00a0\u2026pic.twitter.com/4zDKEUCDa5|last=Pozo|first=Brandon del|date=2018-03-14|website=@BrandondelPozo|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> saying that restraint was a valuable quality in a police officer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/local/2017/05/23/chief-body-cam-video-shows-officers-bravery-and-restraint/339361001/|title=Chief: Body cam video shows officer's restraint|last=Murray|first=Elizabeth|website=Burlington Free Press|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> He also investigated the Vermont State Police Academy for allegations that officers were needlessly being struck unexpectedly in the head during training scenarios, causing a pattern of concussions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vtdigger.org/2019/01/07/recruits-suffer-concussions-hitchhiker-scenario-police-academy-drill/|title=Recruits suffer concussions during 'Hitchhiker Scenario' police academy drill|date=2019-01-07|website=VTDigger|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> As a result, the academy settled a suit with one of the injured students and ceased delivering unexpected blows to the heads of its recruits.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vtdigger.org/2019/10/09/burlington-officer-settles-with-police-academy-for-30000-in-hitchhiker-scenario-suit/|title=Police academy settles for $30,000 in 'hitchhiker scenario' suit|last=Oct 9 2019October 10|first=Ellie French|last2=Footnote|first2=2019 {{!}} One Reader|date=2019-10-09|website=VTDigger|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2019, del Pozo authored an op-ed in ''[[The New York Times]]'' arguing that when confronting persons in crisis armed with knives, police officers should view their firearms as a means to defend themselves and others from harm, rather than the means by which to persuade the person to drop the knife, often accompanied by yelling orders that only escalate the person in crisis.<ref name=\":11\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/13/opinion/police-shootings-guns.html|title=Opinion {{!}} I'm a Police Chief. We Need to Change How Officers View Their Guns.|last=Pozo|first=Brandon del|date=2019-11-13|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-01-17|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Instead, he advocated that officers should have a gun at the ready, but engage with distressed suspects as if the officer was unarmed and had to rely on deescalation and persuasion instead.<ref name=\":11\" /> \n\nA few weeks later, his view was echoed by the Washington Post editorial board, which observed that the present protocol \"is for officers to advance and draw their guns, repeatedly shout 'Drop the knife!' and hope for compliance. But pointing a gun at a person in crisis tends to increase their anxiety and exacerbate the situation, while advancing toward them may put the officer in unnecessary danger.\" The Post repeated del Pozo's observation that, in sum, \"officers should be trained not to point weapons at potentially suicidal people, to move a safe distance away and continue backing away when possible, and to converse with the person rather than shouting commands.\" <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/suicide-by-cop-is-a-persistent-problem-heres-how-to-prevent-it/2020/01/10/dc1a1358-324d-11ea-a053-dc6d944ba776_story.html|title='Suicide by cop' is a persistent problem. Here's how to prevent it|last=The Editorial Board|date=10 January 2020|website=Washington Post|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Both opinion pieces were based on a research report by PERF outlining the potential for such innovations in police tactics to prevent shootings and save lives.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.policeforum.org/suicidebycop|title=Suicide By Cop|website=policeforum.org|access-date=2020-01-18}}</ref>\n\n=== Transparency ===\nAn advocate for greater transparency in policing and government, del Pozo created a police data transparency portal where he discloses a range of raw and processed data about the work of the Burlington Police under a quote by legal philosopher [[Jeremy Waldron]]: \"In a democracy, the accountable agents of the people owe the people an account of what they have been doing, and a refusal to provide this is simple insolence.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonvt.gov/Police/Data|title=BPD Crime Data {{!}} City of Burlington, Vermont|website=burlingtonvt.gov|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref>  He has spoken at the Obama [[White House]] to an audience of police leaders on the value of the practice as part of efforts to implement the recommendations of the President's Task Force on 21st Century Policing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wcax.com/story/32807370/police-chief-del-pozo-reflects-on-trip-to-washington-dc|title=Police Chief Del Pozo reflects on trip to Washington D.C.|last=McGilvery|first=Keith|access-date=2016-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160926072555/http://www.wcax.com/story/32807370/police-chief-del-pozo-reflects-on-trip-to-washington-dc|archive-date=2016-09-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> During his tenure, the police department has made concerted efforts to diversify its rank and file, with moderate success.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/opinion/editorials/2017/01/08/editorial-burlington-polices-diversity-move/96265960/|title=Editorial: Burlington police does diversity|newspaper=Burlington Free Press|access-date=2017-01-10}}</ref>\n\n=== Overseas Intelligence ===\nIn 2005, citing intelligence failures that led to the [[September 11 attacks|9/11 terror attacks]], the NYPD selected del Pozo to create and staff its first intelligence liaison post with the Arab world, based out of Amman, Jordan.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Dickey|first=Christopher|title=Securing the City: Inside America's Best Counterterror Force--The NYPD|publisher=Simon & Schuster|year=2009|isbn=|location=New York|pages=147}}</ref> Embedded with the Jordanian National Police, he responded to [[2005 Amman bombings|suicide bombings at Jordanian hotels]] planned and executed by [[Abu Musab al-Zarqawi]], and an attack on a Roman amphitheater.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Butcher|first=Tim|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/1528110/Terror-in-the-amphitheatre-as-tourists-are-shot.html|title=Terror in the amphitheatre as tourists are shot|journal=Daily Telegraph|date=2006-09-04|access-date=2020-02-12|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref> He also responded to two attacks in Mumbai, India: [[2006 Mumbai train bombings|a 2006 bombing of seven trains]] on the city's commuter rail,<ref>{{Cite book|last=Comiskey|first=John|title=EFFECTIVE STATE, LOCAL, AND TRIBAL POLICE INTELLIGENCE: THE NEW YORK CITY POLICE DEPARTMENT'S INTELLIGENCE ENTERPRISE|publisher=The US Naval Postgraduate School|year=2010|isbn=|location=Monterey, CA|pages=71}}</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/Mumbai-terror-makes-NYPD-Blue/articleshow/1785453.cms</ref> and the [[2008 Mumbai attacks|2008 Lashkar-e-Taiba-led attack on downtown Mumbai]] itself, where a team of gunmen attacked hotels, transportation hubs, tourist areas and a Jewish cultural center. Del Pozo reported his analyses back to the NYPD and other agencies,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=97912059|title=Mumbai Attacks Offer Clues To Security|website=NPR.org|language=en|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref> assessing how these attacks could be replicated by exploiting security vulnerabilities in New York City,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wnyc.org/story/75838-how-safe-are-hotels-and-other-urban-spaces/|title=How Safe Are Hotels and Other Urban Spaces? {{!}} WNYC {{!}} New York Public Radio, Podcasts, Live Streaming Radio, News|website=WNYC|language=en|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref> and what measures could be taken to prevent them.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.utep.edu/clhb/_Files/docs/DHS_Research_in_Brief_Dahl.pdf|title=Counterterrorism and Intelligence|last=|first=|date=|website=Center for Law and Human Behavior, UT el Paso|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> His role was unique in that there was no other US intelligence officer conducting work on behalf of a municipal police department in either region.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Dahl|first=Erik J.|date=2014-07-03|title=Local approaches to counterterrorism: the New York Police Department model|journal=Journal of Policing, Intelligence and Counter Terrorism|volume=9|issue=2|pages=81\u201397|doi=10.1080/18335330.2014.940815|issn=1833-5330}}</ref>\n\n=== Recognition ===\nIn May 2016, the PERF awarded del Pozo its Gary Hayes Memorial Award for his innovation and leadership.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.policeforum.org/assets/docs/Subject_to_Debate/Debate2016/debate_2016_mayjun.pdf|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> He is also an executive fellow at the [[Washington, D.C.|Washington, D.C]].-based [[Police Foundation]], a \"national, independent non-profit organization dedicated to advancing policing through innovation and science.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.policefoundation.org/team_detail/chief-brandon-del-pozo/|title=Chief Brandon del Pozo {{!}} Police Foundation|website=policefoundation.org|language=en-US|access-date=2017-02-01}}</ref> ''[[The New York Times|New York Times]]'' editor and book critic [[Dwight Garner (critic)|Dwight Garner]] characterized del Pozo as \"thoughtful and sane.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/dwightgarner/status/752494957835984896|title=Dwight Garner on Twitter|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref>\n\nHe is presently writing a book about police work for [[Farrar, Straus and Giroux|Farrar, Straus & Giroux]].<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Resignation ==\nDel Pozo resigned as police chief on December 16, 2019, after disclosing that he had used an anonymous Twitter account (\"WinkleWatchers\") to direct approximately eight tweets at a critic of the city leadership, for approximately an hour on July 4, before deleting the tweets and the account within the hour.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/news/2019/12/16/burlington-police-chief-brandon-del-pozo-faces-call-resign-vermont/2662672001/|title=Burlington Police Chief del Pozo resigns: Here's how he got to that point|last=Murray|first=Elizabeth|website=Burlington Free Press|language=en|access-date=2019-12-17}}</ref> When asked by a reporter about the tweets later that July, del Pozo repeatedly denied authorship.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2019/12/12/burlington-police-chief-admits-he-used-an-anonymous-twitter-account-to-taunt-a-critic|title=Burlington Police Chief Admits He Used an Anonymous Twitter Account to Taunt a Critic|last=Lamdin|first=Courtney|website=Seven Days|language=en|access-date=2019-12-17}}</ref> Five months later, when Del Pozo admitted that he authored the tweets, he resigned. In a statement to The New York Times, he said he wrote eight Tweets \u201cin 45 minutes of my life that I wish I could take back, but they taught me that nothing good ever comes from letting social media criticism get under your skin... It was a real lesson learned during a stressful time in my life.\u201d<ref>{{Cite news|last=Cramer|first=Maria|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/11/us/burlington-police-jan-wright-twitter.html|title=Yet Another Vermont Police Chief Quits Over Fake Social Media Accounts|date=2020-02-11|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-02-12|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> \n\nAccording to ''Seven Days'', an attorney suing the city complained that del Pozo didn't list the Twitter account in court filings pertaining to an unrelated use of force lawsuit.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2019/12/13/on-tape-burlington-police-chief-lied-repeatedly-about-twitter-account-in-july-call|title=On Tape, Burlington Police Chief Repeatedly Lied About Twitter Account in July|website=Seven Days|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> The federal court judge reviewing the complaint dismissed it, ruling that the attorney violated good faith by making the complaint,<ref>https://vtdigger.org/2020/01/24/federal-judge-denies-motion-to-sanction-burlington-over-ex-chiefs-twitter-account/</ref> and finding \"no evidence that the omissions had caused any 'discernable [sic] harm.'\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2020/01/22/judge-wont-sanction-burlington-over-anonymous-twitter-account|title=Judge Won't Sanction Burlington Over Anonymous Twitter Account|website=Seven Days}}</ref>\n\nIn his resignation letter, del Pozo stated he would soon complete is doctorate in political philosophy, which he did a month later. He also voiced aspirations to complete his book for [[Farrar, Straus and Giroux|Farrar, Straus & Giroux]], and help establish a research center on policing and public health.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vermontbiz.com/news/2019/december/16/burlington-police-chief-del-pozo-resigns|title=Burlington Police Chief del Pozo resigns|date=2019-12-16|website=Vermont Business Magazine|language=en|access-date=2020-01-03}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nDel Pozo married Sarah Carnevale in 2002.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/03/style/weddings-vows-sarah-carnevale-and-brandon-del-pozo.html|title=WEDDINGS: VOWS; Sarah Carnevale and Brandon del Pozo|last=Ellin|first=Abby|date=2002-03-03|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> They moved to Burlington from the village of [[Cold Spring, New York]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://highlandscurrent.com/2015/08/01/the-paper-interviews-brandon-del-pozo/|title=The Paper Interviews: Brandon del Pozo|last=Turton|first=Michael|website=Highlands Current|access-date=2016-09-29}}</ref> He wrote and directed a narrative short film, ''Sunday 1287'',<ref>{{Citation|title=Sunday 1287|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5232374/|accessdate=2017-07-13}}</ref> which screened at the Middlebury and Vermont International Film Festivals.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mynbc5.com/article/burlington-police-chief-directs-film-to-play-in-vermont-international-film-festival/7022442|title=Burlington Police Chief directs film to play in Vermont International Film Festival|last=Isaacs|first=Abby|date=2016-10-21|newspaper=WPTZ|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref> The film was based on a crime he investigated while commanding a precinct in the New York borough of [[the Bronx]]. In 2018, he suffered multiple serious injuries in a bicycle accident, was evacuated to an intensive care unit by helicopter, and went on to recover and return to full duty in his role.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vtdigger.org/2018/08/12/thousands-athletes-done/|title=I was doing what thousands of athletes have done|last=Aug 12 2018August 13|first=Mark Johnson|last2=Footnotes|first2=2018 {{!}} No Reader|date=2018-08-12|website=VTDigger|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> An outdoors enthusiast,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://rootsrated.com/stories/burlingtons-new-police-chief|title=Burlington's New Police Chief is a Badass|date=2016-05-17|newspaper=RootsRated|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref> he has climbed New Hampshire's [[Four-thousand footers|48 highest mountains]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dartmouthalumnimagazine.com/articles/climb-every-mountain|title=Climb Every Mountain|last=Brandon del Pozo \u201996 {{!}} Jan - Feb 2016|website=Dartmouth Alumni Magazine|language=en|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref> completed the Lake Placid Half Ironman and other triathlons, and written for publications about cycling and climbing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.adirondacklifemag.com/blogs/2016/05/23/cycle-adirondacks/|title=Adirondack Life Blog Archive Cycle Adirondacks - Adirondack Life|website=adirondacklifemag.com|access-date=2016-11-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.adirondacklifemag.com/blogs/2017/04/06/the-ice-man/|title=Adirondack Life Article - The Ice Man - Adirondack Life|website=adirondacklifemag.com|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Del Pozo, Brandon}}\n[[Category:John F. Kennedy School of Government alumni]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:American municipal police chiefs]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Bensonhurst, Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:Dartmouth College alumni]]\n[[Category:Stuyvesant High School alumni]]\n[[Category:John Jay College of Criminal Justice alumni]]\n[[Category:Graduate Center, CUNY alumni]]\n", "name_user": "2601:19b:c500:270::2f28", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Deleted \"executive at Police Force.\"  Link did not provide corroboration.)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brandon_del_Pozo"}
{"title_page": "Ippolito Caffi", "text_new": "{{expand Italian|date=February 2015}}\n[[File:Ippolito Caffi - Snow and Fog on the Grand Canal - WGA03744.jpg|thumb|300px|Snow and Fog on the [[Grand Canal (Venice)|Grand Canal]] (1840)]]\n'''Ippolito Caffi''' (1809\u20131866) was an Italian painter of architectural subjects and seascapes or urban [[vedute]].\n\n==Biography==\nHe was born at [[Belluno]]. His first works were produced at the [[Accademia di Belle Arti di Venezia|Academy of Fine Arts]] of [[Venice]]. By 1830, he had won awards for his vedute at the Academy. He subsequently moved to Rome, made some reputation by his treatise on perspective, as well as by his investigations on [[Roman archaeology]]. In 1843 he visited Greece and the East (Athens, Constantinople, Syria, Egypt, and Malta).<ref>Mostra ''Caffi, Luci di Mediterraneo''.</ref> The first work of his that created a sensation was ''Carnival at Venice''. This was exhibited at Paris in 1846, and was admired for its brilliant effects of light. Other works are his ''Panorama of Rome from Monte Mario'', ''Isthmus of Suez'', and ''Close of the Carnival at Rome''. He joined revolutionary movements in [[Venice]] in 1848, and had to retire into Piedmont. His aim of commemorating in paint the first Italian naval engagement was frustrated when the ''Re d' Italia'', on which he traveled was destroyed on July 20, 1866, by Austro-Venetian fleet at the [[Battle of Lissa (1866)|battle of Lissa]], drowning him along with his comrades.\n\nIn 2005-2006, an exhibition on Ippolito Caffi was held in his native Belluno<ref>[http://www.provincia.belluno.it/nqcontent.cfm?a_id=546  Mostra ''Caffi, Luci di Mediterraneo''].</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*{{cite book| first=Michael| last=Bryan| year=1886| title=''Dictionary of Painters and Engravers, Biographical and Critical'' (Volume I: A-K)| editor = Robert Edmund Graves| pages= 208| publisher=George Bell and Sons|location=York St. #4, Covent Garden, London; Original from Fogg Library, Digitized May 18, 2007 |id= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4GYCAAAAYAAJ| authorlink=}}\n\n==External links==\n(IT) [https://www.pontiart.com/ippolito-caffi-biografia Biography of the Painter Ippolito Caffi], at pontiart.com\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Caffi, Ippolito}}\n[[Category:1814 births]]\n[[Category:1866 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Belluno]]\n[[Category:19th-century Italian painters]]\n[[Category:Italian male painters]]\n[[Category:Venetian painters]]\n[[Category:Italian vedutisti]]\n\n\n{{Italy-painter-19thC-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{expand Italian|date=February 2015}}\n[[File:Ippolito Caffi - Snow and Fog on the Grand Canal - WGA03744.jpg|thumb|300px|Snow and Fog on the [[Grand Canal (Venice)|Grand Canal]] (1840)]]\n'''Ippolito Caffi''' (1809\u20131866) was an Italian painter of architectural subjects and seascapes or urban [[vedute]].\n\n==Biography==\nHe was born at [[Belluno]]. His first works were produced at the [[Accademia di Belle Arti di Venezia|Academy of Fine Arts]] of [[Venice]]. By 1830, he had won awards for his vedute at the Academy. He subsequently moved to Rome, made some reputation by his treatise on perspective, as well as by his investigations on [[Roman archaeology]]. In 1843 he visited Greece and the East (Athens, Constantinople, Syria, Egypt, and Malta).<ref>Mostra ''Caffi, Luci di Mediterraneo''.</ref> The first work of his that created a sensation was ''Carnival at Venice''. This was exhibited at Paris in 1846, and was admired for its brilliant effects of light. Other works are his ''Panorama of Rome from Monte Mario'', ''Isthmus of Suez'', and ''Close of the Carnival at Rome''. He joined revolutionary movements in [[Venice]] in 1848, and had to retire into Piedmont. His aim of commemorating in paint the first Italian naval engagement was frustrated when the ''Re d' Italia'', on which he traveled was destroyed on July 20, 1866, by Austro-Venetian fleet at the [[Battle of Lissa (1866)|battle of Lissa]], drowning him along with his comrades.\n\nIn 2005-2006, an exhibition on Ippolito Caffi was held in his native Belluno<ref>[http://www.provincia.belluno.it/nqcontent.cfm?a_id=546  Mostra ''Caffi, Luci di Mediterraneo''].</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*{{cite book| first=Michael| last=Bryan| year=1886| title=''Dictionary of Painters and Engravers, Biographical and Critical'' (Volume I: A-K)| editor = Robert Edmund Graves| pages= 208| publisher=George Bell and Sons|location=York St. #4, Covent Garden, London; Original from Fogg Library, Digitized May 18, 2007 |id= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4GYCAAAAYAAJ| authorlink=}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat inline|Ippolito Caffi}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Caffi, Ippolito}}\n[[Category:1814 births]]\n[[Category:1866 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Belluno]]\n[[Category:19th-century Italian painters]]\n[[Category:Italian male painters]]\n[[Category:Venetian painters]]\n[[Category:Italian vedutisti]]\n\n\n{{Italy-painter-19thC-stub}}\n", "name_user": "151.24.240.96", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ippolito_Caffi"}
{"title_page": "Erulo Eroli", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=January 2014}}\n\n'''Erulo Eroli''' (August 31, 1854 \u2013 1916)<ref>[http://www.fondazionecarit.it/ Galleries of collection].</ref> was an [[Italy|Italian]] painter.\n\nHe was born in [[Rome]]. His initial studies were in the [[Ospizio di San Michele, Rome|Ospizio di San Michele]] in Rome under professor Ceccarini. He was able to win awards from his Institute and the Ministry of public education for ''Studio di un testa'' and ''Return to his family of a soldier wounded for his family''. His painting of a ''Bacchante'' was awarded a silver medal at the Society of the Fine Arts in Rome. His works also include a candlelight painting titled ''Un Coro di Fanciulli'' and ''Gloria in Excelsis Ave Maria''. The other painting by Eroli found in the Naval Academy of [[Livorno]] is titled ''La Palestro a [[Battle of Lissa (1866)|Lissa]]'', which had been exhibited at the 1883 Exposition in Rome. The subject was an episode during an 1866 battle between the Italian and Austrian navies. Other works included ''A tiger'', ''Cornelio Puio'', and some portraits of ''Cardinal Jacobini'' and ''il Suonatore Arabo''.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Zz0bAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false  ''Dizionario degli Artisti Italiani Viventi: pittori, scultori, e Architetti.''], by Angelo de Gubernatis. Tipe dei Successori Le Monnier, 1889, page 187.</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n(IT) [https://www.pontiart.com/erulo-eroli-biografia Biography of the painter Erulo Eroli], at pontiart.com\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Eroli, Erulo}}\n[[Category:1854 births]]\n[[Category:1916 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century Italian painters]]\n[[Category:Italian male painters]]\n[[Category:20th-century Italian painters]]\n[[Category:Artists from Rome]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=January 2014}}\n\n'''Erulo Eroli''' (August 31, 1854 \u2013 1916)<ref>[http://www.fondazionecarit.it/ Galleries of collection].</ref> was an [[Italy|Italian]] painter.\n\nHe was born in [[Rome]]. His initial studies were in the [[Ospizio di San Michele, Rome|Ospizio di San Michele]] in Rome under professor Ceccarini. He was able to win awards from his Institute and the Ministry of public education for ''Studio di un testa'' and ''Return to his family of a soldier wounded for his family''. His painting of a ''Bacchante'' was awarded a silver medal at the Society of the Fine Arts in Rome. His works also include a candlelight painting titled ''Un Coro di Fanciulli'' and ''Gloria in Excelsis Ave Maria''. The other painting by Eroli found in the Naval Academy of [[Livorno]] is titled ''La Palestro a [[Battle of Lissa (1866)|Lissa]]'', which had been exhibited at the 1883 Exposition in Rome. The subject was an episode during an 1866 battle between the Italian and Austrian navies. Other works included ''A tiger'', ''Cornelio Puio'', and some portraits of ''Cardinal Jacobini'' and ''il Suonatore Arabo''.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Zz0bAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false  ''Dizionario degli Artisti Italiani Viventi: pittori, scultori, e Architetti.''], by Angelo de Gubernatis. Tipe dei Successori Le Monnier, 1889, page 187.</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Eroli, Erulo}}\n[[Category:1854 births]]\n[[Category:1916 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century Italian painters]]\n[[Category:Italian male painters]]\n[[Category:20th-century Italian painters]]\n[[Category:Artists from Rome]]\n", "name_user": "151.24.240.96", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eExternal links)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erulo_Eroli"}
{"title_page": "Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo\n| image                = \n| genre                = [[Animation]]\n| camera               = \n| picture_format       = \n| audio_format         = \n| runtime              = 90 minutes\n| director             = [[Ray Patterson (animator)|Ray Patterson]]<br>[[George Gordon (animator)|George Gordon]]\n| producer             = Art Scott\n| executive_producer   = [[William Hanna]]<br>[[Joseph Barbera]]\n| starring             = \n| voices               = [[Henry Corden]]<br>[[Mel Blanc]]<br>[[Jean Vander Pyl]]<br>[[Gay Autterson]]<br>Joe Baker<br>Wayne Norton<br>[[Marilyn Schreffler]]<br>[[Frank Welker]]<br>Dolores Cantu-Primo\n| theme_music_composer = \n| country              = United States\n| language             = [[English language|English]]\n| network              = [[NBC]]\n| distributor          = [[Taft Broadcasting]]\n| first_aired          = {{start date|1979|12|08}}\n| last_aired           = {{end date|1980|11|15}}\n| num_seasons          = 1\n| num_episodes         = 17 (59 segments)\n| list_episodes        = \n| preceded_by          = ''[[Fred and Barney Meet the Thing]]''\n| followed_by          = ''[[The Flintstone Comedy Show]]''\n| related              = \n| website              = \n}}\n'''''Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo''''' is a 90-minute [[Saturday-morning cartoon|Saturday morning animated]] package show and a [[spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of ''[[The Flintstones]]'' produced by [[Hanna-Barbera]] which aired on [[NBC]] from December 8, 1979 to November 15, 1980.<ref name=Perlmutter>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |page=210}}</ref> It contained the following three segments:\n\n*''[[The New Fred and Barney Show]]'' (a revival of ''The Flintstones'')\n*''[[Fred and Barney Meet the Thing|The Thing]]'' (based on the [[Marvel Comics]] superhero [[Thing (comics)|Thing]])\n*''[[The New Shmoo]]'' (based on the ''[[Li'l Abner]]'' comic strip character [[Shmoo]])\n\nThe show was a repackaging of old episodes of ''The New Fred and Barney Show'' and ''The Thing'' segments (originally broadcast as ''[[Fred and Barney Meet the Thing]]'') combined with episodes of ''The New Shmoo''.<ref name=Woolery>{{cite book |last1=Woolery |first1=George W. |title=Children's Television: The First Thirty-Five Years, 1946-1981 |date=1983 |publisher=Scarecrow Press |isbn=0-8108-1557-5  |url=https://archive.org/details/childrenstelevis0000wool/mode/2up |accessdate=14 March 2020 |page=108}}</ref>\n\nDespite the show's title, the segments remained separate and did not crossover with one another. The characters of [[Fred Flintstone]], [[Barney Rubble]], the [[Thing (comics)|Thing]] and [[Shmoo]] were only featured together in brief bumpers between segments, and the original half-hour episodes of ''The New Shmoo'' were now split into two-parters, allowing more mingling and mixing of the program's individual segments. In 1980, the Shmoo joined Fred and Barney as part-time police officers on the ''Bedrock Cops'' segment of ''[[The Flintstone Comedy Show]]''.\n\nDespite having no narrative connection to the series, a television special called ''The Harlem Globetrotters Meet Snow White'' (also produced by Hanna-Barbera) originally aired in four segments as part of ''Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo'' on September 27, October 4, 11 and 18, 1980.<ref>[https://www.bcdb.com/cartoon/55852-Harlem-Globetrotters-Meet-Snow-White ''The Harlem Globetrotters Meet Snow White''] at [[The Big Cartoon DataBase]], retrieved April 19, 2020.</ref>\n\nLike many animated series created by Hanna-Barbera in the 1970s, the show contained a [[Laugh track#Making their own|laugh track]], one of their last productions to do so.\n\n==Voices==\n\n===''The New Fred and Barney Show''===\n{{main article|The New Fred and Barney Show}}\n*[[Henry Corden]] \u2013 Fred Flintstone\n*[[Jean Vander Pyl]] \u2013 Wilma Flintstone, Pebbles Flintstone\n*[[Mel Blanc]] \u2013 Barney Rubble, Dino\n*[[Gay Autterson]] \u2013 Betty Rubble\n*[[Don Messick]] \u2013 Bamm-Bamm Rubble\n*[[John Stephenson (actor)|John Stephenson]] \u2013 Mr. Slate\n\n===''The Thing''===\n{{main article|Fred and Barney Meet the Thing}}\n*Wayne Norton \u2013 Benjy Grimm\n*Joe Baker \u2013 The Thing\n*Noelle North \u2013 Kelly\n*[[Marilyn Schreffler]] \u2013 Betty, Miss Twilly\n*[[John Erwin]] \u2013 Ronald Radford\n*[[Art Metrano]] \u2013 Spike\n*Michael Sheehan \u2013 Turkey\n*[[John Stephenson (actor)|John Stephenson]] \u2013 Dr. Harkness, Stretch\n\n===''The New Shmoo''===\n{{main article|The New Shmoo}}\n*[[Frank Welker]] \u2013 Shmoo\n*Dolores Cantu-Primo \u2013 Nita\n*[[Bill Idelson]] \u2013 Mickey\n*[[Chuck McCann]] \u2013 Billy Joe\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|id=0298649|title=Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo}}\n*{{tv.com show|fred-and-barney-meet-the-shmoo|Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo}}\n*[http://www.bcdb.com/cartoons/Hanna-Barbera_Studios/D-F/Fred_and_Barney_Meet_the_Shmoo/index.html ''Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo''] at the [[The Big Cartoon DataBase|Big Cartoon DataBase]]\n\n{{The Flintstones}}\n{{Li'l Abner}}\n{{Children's programming on NBC in the 1980s}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fred And Barney Meet The Shmoo}}\n[[Category:The Flintstones spin-offs]]\n[[Category:1979 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1980 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:1970s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:1980s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:American animated television spin-offs]]\n[[Category:NBC original programming]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Li'l Abner]]\n[[Category:Television series by Hanna-Barbera]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Crossover animated television series]]\n[[Category:Television series set in prehistory]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo\n| image                = \n| genre                = [[Animation]]\n| camera               = \n| picture_format       = \n| audio_format         = \n| runtime              = 90 minutes\n| director             = [[Ray Patterson (animator)|Ray Patterson]]<br>[[George Gordon (animator)|George Gordon]]\n| producer             = Art Scott\n| executive_producer   = [[William Hanna]]<br>[[Joseph Barbera]]\n| starring             = \n| voices               = [[Henry Corden]]<br>[[Mel Blanc]]<br>[[Jean Vander Pyl]]<br>[[Gay Autterson]]<br>Joe Baker<br>Wayne Norton<br>[[Marilyn Schreffler]]<br>[[Frank Welker]]<br>Dolores Cantu-Primo\n| theme_music_composer = \n| country              = United States\n| language             = [[English language|English]]\n| network              = [[NBC]]\n| distributor          = [[Taft Broadcasting]]\n| first_aired          = {{start date|1979|12|08}}\n| last_aired           = {{end date|1980|11|15}}\n| num_seasons          = 1\n| num_episodes         = 17 (59 segments)\n| list_episodes        = \n| preceded_by          = ''[[Fred and Barney Meet the Thing]]''\n| followed_by          = ''[[The Flintstone Comedy Show]]''\n| related              = \n| website              = \n}}\n'''''Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo''''' is a 90-minute [[Saturday-morning cartoon|Saturday morning animated]] package show and a [[spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of ''[[The Flintstones]]'' produced by [[Hanna-Barbera]] which aired on [[NBC]] from December 8, 1979 to November 15, 1980.<ref name=Perlmutter>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |page=210}}</ref> It contained the following three segments:\n\n*''[[The New Fred and Barney Show]]'' (a revival of ''The Flintstones'')\n*''[[Fred and Barney Meet the Thing|The Thing]]'' (based on the [[Marvel Comics]] superhero [[Thing (comics)|Thing]])\n*''[[The New Shmoo]]'' (based on the ''[[Li'l Abner]]'' comic strip character [[Shmoo]])\n\nThe show was a repackaging of old episodes of ''The New Fred and Barney Show'' and ''The Thing'' segments (originally broadcast as ''[[Fred and Barney Meet the Thing]]'') combined with episodes of ''The New Shmoo''.<ref name=Woolery>{{cite book |last1=Woolery |first1=George W. |title=Children's Television: The First Thirty-Five Years, 1946-1981 |date=1983 |publisher=Scarecrow Press |isbn=0-8108-1557-5  |url=https://archive.org/details/childrenstelevis0000wool/mode/2up |accessdate=14 March 2020 |page=108}}</ref>\n\nDespite the show's title, the segments remained separate and did not crossover with one another. The characters of [[Fred Flintstone]], [[Barney Rubble]], the [[Thing (comics)|Thing]] and [[Shmoo]] were only featured together in brief bumpers between segments, and the original half-hour episodes of ''The New Shmoo'' were now split into two-parters, allowing more mingling and mixing of the program's individual segments. In 1980, the Shmoo joined Fred and Barney as part-time police officers on the ''Bedrock Cops'' segment of ''[[The Flintstone Comedy Show]]''.\n\nA television special called ''The Harlem Globetrotters Meet Snow White'' (also produced by Hanna-Barbera) originally aired in four segments as part of ''Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo'' on September 27, October 4, 11 and 18, 1980.<ref>[https://www.bcdb.com/cartoon/55852-Harlem-Globetrotters-Meet-Snow-White ''The Harlem Globetrotters Meet Snow White''] at [[The Big Cartoon DataBase]], retrieved April 19, 2020.</ref>\n\nLike many animated series created by Hanna-Barbera in the 1970s, the show contained a [[Laugh track#Making their own|laugh track]], one of their last productions to do so.\n\n==Voices==\n\n===''The New Fred and Barney Show''===\n{{main article|The New Fred and Barney Show}}\n*[[Henry Corden]] \u2013 Fred Flintstone\n*[[Jean Vander Pyl]] \u2013 Wilma Flintstone, Pebbles Flintstone\n*[[Mel Blanc]] \u2013 Barney Rubble, Dino\n*[[Gay Autterson]] \u2013 Betty Rubble\n*[[Don Messick]] \u2013 Bamm-Bamm Rubble\n*[[John Stephenson (actor)|John Stephenson]] \u2013 Mr. Slate\n\n===''The Thing''===\n{{main article|Fred and Barney Meet the Thing}}\n*Wayne Norton \u2013 Benjy Grimm\n*Joe Baker \u2013 The Thing\n*Noelle North \u2013 Kelly\n*[[Marilyn Schreffler]] \u2013 Betty, Miss Twilly\n*[[John Erwin]] \u2013 Ronald Radford\n*[[Art Metrano]] \u2013 Spike\n*Michael Sheehan \u2013 Turkey\n*[[John Stephenson (actor)|John Stephenson]] \u2013 Dr. Harkness, Stretch\n\n===''The New Shmoo''===\n{{main article|The New Shmoo}}\n*[[Frank Welker]] \u2013 Shmoo\n*Dolores Cantu-Primo \u2013 Nita\n*[[Bill Idelson]] \u2013 Mickey\n*[[Chuck McCann]] \u2013 Billy Joe\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|id=0298649|title=Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo}}\n*{{tv.com show|fred-and-barney-meet-the-shmoo|Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo}}\n*[http://www.bcdb.com/cartoons/Hanna-Barbera_Studios/D-F/Fred_and_Barney_Meet_the_Shmoo/index.html ''Fred and Barney Meet the Shmoo''] at the [[The Big Cartoon DataBase|Big Cartoon DataBase]]\n\n{{The Flintstones}}\n{{Li'l Abner}}\n{{Children's programming on NBC in the 1980s}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fred And Barney Meet The Shmoo}}\n[[Category:The Flintstones spin-offs]]\n[[Category:1979 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1980 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:1970s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:1980s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:American animated television spin-offs]]\n[[Category:NBC original programming]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Li'l Abner]]\n[[Category:Television series by Hanna-Barbera]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Crossover animated television series]]\n[[Category:Television series set in prehistory]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fred_and_Barney_Meet_the_Shmoo"}
{"title_page": "B. R. Shetty", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Bavaguthu Raghuram Shetty\n| image              = File:Dr BR Shetty Official Pic.jpg\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1942|08|01|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Udupi]], [[Madras Presidency]], [[British India]] (now [[Karnataka]], [[India]])\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| occupation         = \n| known_for          = Founder [[NMC Health]], [[UAE Exchange]], [[Finablr]]\n| website            = {{url|brshetty.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Bavaguthu Raghuram Shetty''' (born 1 August 1942) is an Indian-born former [[billionaire]] businessman, and the founder of a number of companies based in the United Arab Emirates. He is founder of [[Abu Dhabi]]-based [[NMC Health]],<ref name=national/> and [[UAE Exchange]].<ref name=\"Indian Rich List in full - ArabianBusiness.com\"/> He is also the founder and chairman of Neopharma and BRS Ventures.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://businessworld.in/article/-I-Want-To-Be-The-No-1-Healthcare-Provider-In-India-Over-The-Next-10-Years-/23-03-2018-144373/| title=I Want To Be The No. 1 Healthcare Provider in India Over The Next 10 Years| author=Paramita Chatterjee, Suman K Jha| date=23 March 2018| publisher=BusinessWorld| access-date=8 May 2018| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180509012947/http://businessworld.in/article/-I-Want-To-Be-The-No-1-Healthcare-Provider-In-India-Over-The-Next-10-Years-/23-03-2018-144373/| archive-date=9 May 2018|url-status = live}}</ref> He is founder and co-chairman of [[Finablr]]. In 2018, the UAE Exchange brand became part of the financial services holding company, Finablr.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.forbesmiddleeast.com/en/billionaire-b-r-shetty-launches-new-financial-firms-holding-company-finablr/| title=Billionaire B.R. Shetty Launches New Financial Firms Holding Company Finablr| author=Mary Sophia| date=24 April 2018| publisher=Forbes Middle East| access-date=24 August 2018| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180825073919/https://www.forbesmiddleeast.com/en/billionaire-b-r-shetty-launches-new-financial-firms-holding-company-finablr/| archive-date=25 August 2018|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nShetty's initial interest in 1975 was in hospitals and hospitality, and has since diversified into pharmaceuticals, financial services, retail, advertising and information technology.<ref name=\"Indian Rich List in full - ArabianBusiness.com\">{{cite web | url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/indian-rich-list-in-full-342165.html#.V3JIbLh9600 | title=Indian Rich List in full - ArabianBusiness.com | publisher=ArabianBusiness | accessdate=28 June 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424235811/http://www.arabianbusiness.com/indian-rich-list-in-full-342165.html#.V3JIbLh9600 | archive-date=24 April 2016 |url-status = live}}</ref> He was included on the ''[[Forbes]]'' list of India's 100 Richest People in 2015 and was listed as the 42nd richest person in 2020.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/br-shetty/| title=#47 B.R. Shetty| work=Forbes| accessdate=14 April 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161228013207/http://www.forbes.com/profile/br-shetty/| archive-date=28 December 2016|url-status = live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/br-shetty/#6862cc8b6cc7| title=#42 B.R. Shetty| work=Forbes| accessdate=20 February 2020| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514112322/https://www.forbes.com/profile/br-shetty/#6862cc8b6cc7| archive-date=14 May 2019| url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThere are allegations of misappropriation by Shetty at his companies and was forced to resign from his director positions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/how-indian-billionaire-bavaguthu-raghuram-shetty-who-owned-2-floors-of-burj-khalifa-went-bust-2182896 | title=How Indian billionaire Bavaguthu Raghuram Shetty went bust}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arabianbusiness.com/healthcare/440371-billionaire-br-shetty-resigns-from-abu-dhabis-nmc-health | title=Billionaire BR Shetty resigns from Abu Dhabi's NMC Health}}</ref> On April 8, 2020, NMC Health went into Administration in UK due to the insolvency of the company due to alleged frauds committed by Shetty.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nmc-insolvency-proceedings-inevitable-hospital-143125949.html | title=NMC into Administration}}</ref>\nDue to sharp drop in the share prices and Shetty pledging the shares for debts that he had incurred, it is believed that his net worth has fallen to fraction of the earlier estimate of $3.5 billion.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gulfbusiness.com/uae-based-br-shettys-fortune-drops-1-5bn-since-muddy-waters-attack/ | title=\"BR Shetty's fortune drops by $1.5 Billion| date=26 January 2020}}</ref> Consequently, Forbes has dropped Shetty from its 2020 annual list of billionaires.\n\nShetty fled the UAE to his native country, India, fearing legal procedure there by lender banks, including Dubai Islamic Bank and ADCB.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arabianbusiness.com/banking-finance/444829-nmc-health-goes-into-administration-after-succumbing-to-creditors|title=NMC Health goes into administration after succumbing to creditors|website=ArabianBusiness.com}}</ref> On 15 April 2020,  Abu Dhabi Commercial Bank filed criminal complaint against NMC Health with the Attorney General's Office of UAE.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-nmc-health-adcb-crime-idUSKCN21X1BY|title=ADCB files criminal complaint against individuals over NMC Health|date=2020-04-15|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-04-16|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/corporate/nmcs-br-shetty-5-others-face-fraud-forgery-charges|title=NMC's BR Shetty, 5 others face fraud, forgery charges|last=John|first=Issac|website=Khaleej Times|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> Now, Indian agencies have initiated probe to identify potential risks to Indian banks, if any.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newsd.in/after-cases-in-uae-b-r-shetty-on-radar-of-indian-probe-agencies/|title=After cases in UAE, BR Shetty on radar of Indian probe agencies|date=2020-04-16|website=News and Analysis from India. A Refreshing approach to news.|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nShetty was born in [[Kapu, Karnataka|Kapu]], [[Udupi]] to [[Tulu language|Tulu]] speaking parents Shambhu Shetty and Koosamma Shetty on 1 August 1942 to an ethnic [[Tuluva]] family.<ref name = \"Mangalorean Tuluva\">{{cite web |url=http://www.mangaloretoday.com/gulfnews/Mangalorean-Tuluva-B-R-Shetty-buys-Travelex-for-1-billion.html |title=Mangalorean Tuluva B R Shetty Buy's Travelex for 1 billion |date=14 June 2015 |accessdate=12 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802204342/http://www.mangaloretoday.com/gulfnews/Mangalorean-Tuluva-B-R-Shetty-buys-Travelex-for-1-billion.html |archive-date=2 August 2017 |url-status = live}}</ref> Shetty completed his pharmaceutical education in [[India]] and also served as the Vice-Chairman of the Municipal Council in Udupi. He married Chandrakumari Shetty and has four children.<ref name=\"Journey - Dr. B. R. Shetty\">{{cite web | url=http://www.brshetty.com/journey/ | title=Journey \u2013 Dr. B. R. Shetty | accessdate=28 June 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614205457/http://www.brshetty.com/journey/ | archive-date=14 June 2016 |url-status = live}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nShetty immigrated to the UAE in 1973. After working as the country's first medical representative,<ref name=national/> he founded [[NMC Health|New Medical Centre Health]] (NMC) in 1975 to fill the need for personalized, cost-effective healthcare accessible to all.<ref name=national/><ref name=namma>{{cite web| url=http://namma.tv/dr-b-r-shetty-to-build-abu-dhabis-first-medical-university-in-honour-of-sheikh-zayed/| title=Dr B.R.Shetty to build Abu Dhabi's first medical university in honour of Sheikh Zayed| date=24 June 2016| publisher=NamMa TV| accessdate=2 May 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802174516/http://namma.tv/dr-b-r-shetty-to-build-abu-dhabis-first-medical-university-in-honour-of-sheikh-zayed/| archive-date=2 August 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> At that time, his wife was the only doctor in the clinic.<ref name=emi/> NMC is now the largest private healthcare provider in the UAE with over four million patients annually across 45 facilities spread over 12 cities and 8 countries, including UAE, KSA, Oman, Spain, Italy, Denmark, Colombia and Brazil. It is the first healthcare company from the Gulf Cooperation Countries (GCC) and the first company from Abu Dhabi to be listed on the premium segment of the [[London Stock Exchange]] and was part of the coveted [[FTSE 100 Index]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2017/09/02/gulf-private-hospitals-group-nmc-eyes-uk-launch-leap-ftse-100/|title=Gulf private hospitals group NMC eyes UK launch after leap into FTSE 100|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=2 September 2017|access-date=24 September 2017|first=Iain|last=Withers|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170913030605/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2017/09/02/gulf-private-hospitals-group-nmc-eyes-uk-launch-leap-ftse-100/|archive-date=13 September 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> Consequent to the request from the board of directors of NMC and on going investigation of potential financial irregularities, the company was de-listed from London Stock Exchange and was removed from FTSE 100 index. \n\nShetty established the [[UAE Exchange]] in 1980 in an attempt to ease the process of sending money by the expats to their families in their respective home countries. By 2016, it had expanded into over 31 countries and had approximately 800 direct offices. In 2014, it did over US$50 billion collectively in money remittance and exchange volumes.<ref name=emi>{{cite web| url=http://www.emirates247.com/news/emirates/dubai-dreams-from-jobless-medical-rep-to-billions-br-shetty-2016-08-10-1.638590| title=Dubai Dreams: From jobless medical rep to billions - BR Shetty| author=VM Sathish| date=10 August 2016| publisher=Emirates 24/7| accessdate=2 May 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170606205018/http://www.emirates247.com/news/emirates/dubai-dreams-from-jobless-medical-rep-to-billions-br-shetty-2016-08-10-1.638590| archive-date=6 June 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> Shetty acquired [[Travelex]], a major foreign exchange company, in 2014.<ref name=national>{{cite web| url=http://www.thenational.ae/business/industry-insights/economics/br-shetty-the-astute-businessman-who-turned-8-into-1bn#full| title=BR Shetty, the astute businessman who turned $8 into $1bn| author=Frank Kane| date=1 July 2014| publisher=The National| accessdate=2 May 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170428185222/http://www.thenational.ae/business/industry-insights/economics/br-shetty-the-astute-businessman-who-turned-8-into-1bn#full| archive-date=28 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref><ref name=khal/> Travelex has a global footprint including 1500 stores and 1300 ATMs across 27 countries. \n\nIn 2003, Shetty founded NMC Neopharma, a UAE based pharmaceutical manufacturer.<ref name=emi/> Inaugurated by the then President of India, [[A. P. J. Abdul Kalam]] in Abu Dhabi, Neopharma is centered on using the concept of modular manufacturing following global benchmarks in manufacturing technology and putting in place efficient control mechanisms. Neopharma has a research and development wing and works to provide quality medicines at affordable prices. The company also contracts manufacturing for international pharmaceutical companies as well as generic brands for companies including, but not limited to, [[Merck Group|Merck]], [[Pfizer]], [[AstraZeneca]], and [[Boots UK]].<ref name=emi/>\n\nIn 2012, Shetty led NMC through an [[initial public offering|IPO]] on the [[London Stock Exchange]], which raised $330 million. The funds went towards building a specialty hospital in [[Khalifa City]], Abu Dhabi.<ref name=gulfnews>{{cite web| url=http://gulfnews.com/business/sectors/general/dr-b-r-shetty-to-expand-his-nmc-group-in-uae-and-gcc-1.1400467| title=Dr B.R. Shetty to expand his NMC group in UAE and GCC| author=Fareed Rahman| date=18 October 2014| publisher=Gulf News| accessdate=2 May 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161006162305/http://gulfnews.com/business/sectors/general/dr-b-r-shetty-to-expand-his-nmc-group-in-uae-and-gcc-1.1400467| archive-date=6 October 2016|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2016, Shetty announced that he was building the first medical university in Abu Dhabi in honor of [[Zayed bin Sultan Al Nahyan|Sheikh Zayed]].<ref name=namma/> That same month, he was elected to be chairman of the Indian Business/Professional Group.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.bfirst.in/news/diaspora/8815/br-shetty-wants-promote-india-uae-ties-through-ibpg| title=BR Shetty wants to promote India-UAE ties through IBPG| date=7 June 2016| publisher=Bfirst| accessdate=2 May 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925083522/http://www.bfirst.in/news/diaspora/8815/br-shetty-wants-promote-india-uae-ties-through-ibpg| archive-date=25 September 2017| url-status=dead}}</ref> In August 2016, Shetty announced that he was building a 400-bed super-specialty hospital in Udupi in Karnataka through B R S Ventures.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.mangalorean.com/dr-br-shetty-build-400-bed-super-speciality-hospital-udupi/| title=Dr BR Shetty to Build 400-bed Super-specialty hospital in Udupi| date=25 August 2016| publisher=Mangalorean| accessdate=2 May 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925132051/https://www.mangalorean.com/dr-br-shetty-build-400-bed-super-speciality-hospital-udupi/| archive-date=25 September 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> Shetty also owned a hospital in [[Alexandria]], two hospitals in Nepal, and acquired a hospital in Cairo as part of his personal portfolio under the same company.<ref name=gulfnews/>\n\nIn August 2019, BRS Ventures announced plans to invest $5 billion in developing healthcare facilities across India.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.businesstoday.in/current/corporate/jang-sangh-hand-billionaire-b-r-shetty-5-billion-dollar-investments-in-indian-healthcare/story/373353.html | title=Old Jan Sangh hand, billionaire B R Shetty plans $5 billion investment in Indian healthcare | publisher=Business Today | accessdate=25 August 2019 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825084836/https://www.businesstoday.in/current/corporate/jang-sangh-hand-billionaire-b-r-shetty-5-billion-dollar-investments-in-indian-healthcare/story/373353.html | archive-date=25 August 2019 |url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2020, [[Bloomberg News]] report casted doubts on his real holding amidst the short-selling of NMC Health by [[Muddy Waters Research]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/business/a-jet-setting-billionaire-had-it-all-then-carson-block-came-along/articleshow/74204580.cms|title=Jet-setting billionaire Bavaguthu Raghuram Shetty had it all. Then Carson Block came along| publisher=Bloomberg| accessdate= 20 February 2020}}</ref> Also in February 2020, Shetty was ousted from the NMC Health board following a corporate governance scandal over his holdings in the company.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Correspondent|first=Ben Martin, Senior City|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/nmcs-founder-forced-out-over-shares-scandal-cr59jz2s6|title=NMC's founder forced out over shares scandal|access-date=2020-02-25|language=en|issn=0140-0460}}</ref>\n\nOn April 8, 2020, NMC went into Administration in UK due to the insolvency of the company due to alleged frauds committed by Shetty.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nmc-insolvency-proceedings-inevitable-hospital-143125949.html|title=NMC Heads to Administration After Giving In to Creditor Demands|website=finance.yahoo.com}}</ref>\n\n==Other activities==\nShetty has invested in a medical institution in the north Indian state of Uttarakhand. He is the founder and patron of the Indian Pharmaceutical Association in the Emirates, and is a member of the Advisory Board (Financial Sector), Economic Department, Government of Dubai, UAE and the Pharmaceutical Committee, Dubai. He is also the chairman of [[Abu Dhabi Indian School]] and Bright Riders School.<ref name=\"Indian tycoons storm Arabian Business Expat Power List 2011 - ArabianBusiness.com\">{{cite web | url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/indian-tycoons-storm-arabian-business-expat-power-list-2011-383132.html#.V3JKfbh9600 | title=Indian tycoons storm Arabian Business Expat Power List 2011 - ArabianBusiness.com | publisher=ArabianBusiness | accessdate=28 June 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815070908/http://www.arabianbusiness.com/indian-tycoons-storm-arabian-business-expat-power-list-2011-383132.html#.V3JKfbh9600 | archive-date=15 August 2016 |url-status = live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://brightriders.ae/?page_id=176|title=Chairman's Message {{!}} Bright Riders School, Abu Dhabi|website=brightriders.ae|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802164450/http://brightriders.ae/?page_id=176|archive-date=2 August 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2015, Shetty was elected as the Chairman to the board of directors of UAE Exchange.<ref name=khal>{{cite web|url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/dr-br-shetty-takes-over-as-chairman-of-uae-exchange|title=Dr B.R. Shetty takes over as chairman of UAE Exchange|work=Khaleej Times|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085905/http://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/dr-br-shetty-takes-over-as-chairman-of-uae-exchange|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/uae-exchange-appoints-b-r-shetty-as-chairman-promoth-manghat-as-ceo/articleshow/48652739.cms|title=UAE Exchange appoints B R Shetty as Chairman, Promoth Manghat as CEO|newspaper=The Economic Times|date=24 August 2015|publisher=Economic Times India|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424090633/http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/uae-exchange-appoints-b-r-shetty-as-chairman-promoth-manghat-as-ceo/articleshow/48652739.cms|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> He was named chairman of The Indian Business/Professional Group in June 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newskarnataka.com/nri/dr-b-r-shetty-to-head-the-indian-businessprofessional-group|title=Dr B R Shetty to head The Indian Business/Professional Group|publisher=News Karnataka|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085646/http://www.newskarnataka.com/nri/dr-b-r-shetty-to-head-the-indian-businessprofessional-group|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> H. H. Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid al Maktoum nominated Shetty as a member of the UAE medical council in September 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.bfirst.in/news/2016_09_09/12860|title=Businessman BR Shetty nominated to medical council by PM of Dubai|publisher=Bfirst}}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, Shetty announced that he would invest Rs 1000 crore ($157.3 million) to produce a film with director [[V. A. Shrikumar Menon]]. The film, starring [[Mohanlal]], was to be based on the novel [[Randamoozham]], a retelling of [[Mahabharata]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Billionaire B. R. Shetty aims for $1 billion in revenue from Indian film epic|url=https://in.reuters.com/article/nmc-health-shetty-film/billionaire-b-r-shetty-aims-for-1-billion-in-revenue-from-indian-film-epic-idINKBN18V0SR|access-date=28 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171027181423/https://in.reuters.com/article/nmc-health-shetty-film/billionaire-b-r-shetty-aims-for-1-billion-in-revenue-from-indian-film-epic-idINKBN18V0SR|archive-date=27 October 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\nIn May 2019, however, the film was shelved due to creative issues.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mohanlal's Rs 1000 crore film project 'Randamoozham' shelved|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2019/apr/03/mohanlals-rs-1000-crore-film-project-randamoozham-shelved-1959795.html|access-date=20 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190805223955/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2019/apr/03/mohanlals-rs-1000-crore-film-project-randamoozham-shelved-1959795.html|archive-date=5 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and recognition ==\n{{Overly detailed|Section|date=February 2020}}\nIn 2005, Shetty was awarded the highest civilian distinction in the Emirate, the [[Abu Dhabi Awards]].<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.thenational.ae/uae/abu-dhabi-awards-b-r-shetty-1.119120 | title = Abu Dhabi Awards: B R Shetty | date = 23 May 2015 | work = The National | access-date = 23 September 2019 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190923071607/https://www.thenational.ae/uae/abu-dhabi-awards-b-r-shetty-1.119120 | archive-date = 23 September 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref> Given by H. H. Sheikh [[Mohammed bin Zayed Al Nahyan]], the Crown Prince of Abu Dhabi, the first year the distinction was awarded.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenational.ae/uae/abu-dhabi-awards-b-r-shetty|title=Abu Dhabi Awards: B R Shetty|publisher=The National|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170422235344/http://www.thenational.ae/uae/abu-dhabi-awards-b-r-shetty|archive-date=22 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> Also in 2005, U.S. India Friendship Society presented Shetty the Distinguished Entrepreneur Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neopharmauae.com/en/news.asp?News_Id=173-Dr.-B.R.-Shetty-received-The-Distinguished-Entrepreneur-Award-from-the-US-India-Friendship-Society-|title=Dr. B.R. Shetty received The Distinguished Entrepreneur Award from the US India Friendship Society|publisher=Neopharma|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424173745/http://www.neopharmauae.com/en/news.asp?News_Id=173-Dr.-B.R.-Shetty-received-The-Distinguished-Entrepreneur-Award-from-the-US-India-Friendship-Society-|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = dead}}</ref>\n\nShetty was honoured by the [[Pravasi Bharatiya Samman]] in 2007.<ref name=\"The recipients of Pravasi Bharatiya Samman - Times of India\">{{cite web | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/The-recipients-of-Pravasi-Bharatiya-Samman/articleshow/1113368.cms | title=The recipients of Pravasi Bharatiya Samman \u2013 Times of India | work=Times of India| accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"New Delhi B R Shetty Among Padma Shree Awardees\">{{cite web | url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/news_disp.asp?n_id=56080 | title=New Delhi B R Shetty Among Padma Shree Awardees | publisher=Daijiworld Media Pvt Ltd Mangalore | accessdate=28 June 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303170744/http://www.daijiworld.com/news/news_disp.asp?n_id=56080 | archive-date=3 March 2016 |url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nErnst & Young Middle East honored Shetty with the Entrepreneur of the year finalist award in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.emirates247.com/eb247/companies-markets/five-uae-execs-in-running-for-ernst-young-award-2008-01-17-1.216304|title=Five UAE execs in running for Ernst & Young award|publisher=Emirates 24/7|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085817/http://www.emirates247.com/eb247/companies-markets/five-uae-execs-in-running-for-ernst-young-award-2008-01-17-1.216304|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nShetty received the [[Padma Shri|Padmashree]] awarded by the [[President of India]] in 2009 for his contribution in the field of trade and industry.<ref name=\"IBPC Felicitates Padma Shri Award Winners - Khaleej Times\">{{cite web | url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/ibpc-felicitates-padma-shri-award-winners | title=IBPC Felicitates Padma Shri Award Winners \u2013 Khaleej Times | work=Khaleej Times| accessdate=28 June 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160808123305/http://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/ibpc-felicitates-padma-shri-award-winners | archive-date=8 August 2016 |url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2011, he received the Asian Achievers Award from the Human Achievers Foundation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/article/20110713/ARTICLE/307139999/1002|title=Asian Achievers Awards for Dhahi Khalfan, others|work=Khaleej Times|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424174100/http://www.khaleejtimes.com/article/20110713/ARTICLE/307139999/1002|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2012, Pharma Leaders founded by Satya Brahma declared Shetty as Global Indian of the Year along with [[Kiran Mazumdar-Shaw|Kiran Mazumdar Shaw]] at 5th Annual Pharmaceutical Leadership Summit & Pharma Leaders Business Leadership Awards 2012 in Mumbai.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pharmaleaders.tv/biocon-chief-dr-kiran-majumdar-shaw-nmc-chief-dr-b-r-shetty-declared-global-indian-of-the-year-2/|title=Biocon Chief Dr. Kiran Majumdar Shaw & NMC Chief Dr B.R.Shetty Declared Global Indian of the Year {{!}} Pharmaleaders TV|website=pharmaleaders.tv|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171024205347/http://pharmaleaders.tv/biocon-chief-dr-kiran-majumdar-shaw-nmc-chief-dr-b-r-shetty-declared-global-indian-of-the-year-2/|archive-date=24 October 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, Shetty was recognized as one of Asia's most promising leaders at the Asian Brand & Leadership Summit.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=189157|title=UAE Exchange named leader, most promising brand in Asia|publisher=Daiji World|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085721/http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=189157|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> In March 2013, he was awarded the International Achievers Summit's Lifetime Achievement Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nmctrading.com/dr-b-r-shetty-receives-lifetime-achievement-award/|title=Dr. B.R. Shetty receives Lifetime Achievement Award|publisher=NMC Trading|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424174516/http://www.nmctrading.com/dr-b-r-shetty-receives-lifetime-achievement-award/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> That same year, Shetty received the Asian Business Leadership Forum India-UAE Business Icons Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ablfawards.com/2013-winners/|title=ABLF Awards 2013 Winners|publisher=ABLF|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161211033716/http://www.ablfawards.com/2013-winners/|archive-date=11 December 2016|url-status = dead}}</ref> He also received the 2013 Frost & Sullivan Lifetime Achievement Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.frost.com/prod/servlet/press-release.pag?docid=291322634|title=Dr. B R Shetty honoured with Frost & Sullivan - Lifetime Achievement Award for the Year 2013|publisher=Frost & Sullivan|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170425031103/https://www.frost.com/prod/servlet/press-release.pag?docid=291322634|archive-date=25 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Forbes Middle East recognized Shetty with the Top Indian Leaders in the UAE Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbesmiddleeast.com/forbes-middle-east-unveils-top-indian-leaders-in-the-arab-region|title=Forbes Middle East Reveals Top Indian Leaders in the Arab World|website=Forbes Middle East|publisher=Forbes|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> He also received the Lakshya Business Visionary Award in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/getahead/report/achievers-from-salesman-to-biz-tycoon-a-serial-entrepreneurs-success-mantras/20141105.htm|title=From salesman to biz tycoon: A serial entrepreneur's success mantras|publisher=Rediff|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424173734/http://www.rediff.com/getahead/report/achievers-from-salesman-to-biz-tycoon-a-serial-entrepreneurs-success-mantras/20141105.htm|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> That same year, Shetty was recognized with the International Achievement Award at the Indian Innovator Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/entmagazineme/docs/entrepreneur_middle_east_january_20|title=Indian Innovator Awards 2014|publisher=Entrepreneur Middle East|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424173725/https://issuu.com/entmagazineme/docs/entrepreneur_middle_east_january_20|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2015, the Indian Club - Bahrain recognized Shetty with a Centenary Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=295424|title=Bahrain : Dr Kalam presents Indian Club Centenary awards to Colaco, B R Shetty|publisher=Daiji World|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085429/http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=295424|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> He received the Deal of the Year Award at the 2015 Indian CEO Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/sunil-vaswani-takes-top-honours-at-indian-ceo-awards-582410.html|title=Sunil Vaswani takes top honours at Indian CEO Awards|publisher=Arabian Business|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008135040/http://www.arabianbusiness.com/sunil-vaswani-takes-top-honours-at-indian-ceo-awards-582410.html|archive-date=8 October 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> In June 2015, Shetty received the Business Personality of the Year award from Crowe Horwath International.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nmchealth.com/dr-b-r-shetty-has-received-the-prestigious-business-personality-of-the-year-award/|title=Dr. B.R. Shetty has received the prestigious Business Personality of the Year award|publisher=NMV Health|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150805020024/http://www.nmchealth.com/dr-b-r-shetty-has-received-the-prestigious-business-personality-of-the-year-award/|archive-date=5 August 2015|url-status = dead}}</ref> That same month, Shetty received the Arabian Indian Czars award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2015-06-18/news/63567767_1_fadnavis-sunil-vaswani-rizwan-sajan|title=Arabian Indian Czars Award: Times Now felicitates successful Indians in Middle East|work=The Economic Times|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151018060431/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2015-06-18/news/63567767_1_fadnavis-sunil-vaswani-rizwan-sajan|archive-date=18 October 2015|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nShetty received the Global Indian Achiever Award in 2015 from H. H. Sheikh Nahyan Bin Mubarak al Nahyan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nmchealth.com/dr-b-r-shetty-honoured-global-indian-achiever-award/|title=Dr. B R Shetty honoured with Global Indian Achiever Award|publisher=NMC Health|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171031042109/http://www.nmchealth.com/dr-b-r-shetty-honoured-global-indian-achiever-award/|archive-date=31 October 2017|url-status = dead}}</ref> Also in 2015, H. H. Prince Faisal Bin Saud Bin Musaed Bin Abdulaziz presented Shetty with the National Cultural Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sauress.com/en/saudigazette/240107|title=Indian tycoon Shetty is honored with National Cultural Award|work=The Saudi Gazette|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424173839/http://www.sauress.com/en/saudigazette/240107|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> Shetty's company, NMC Healthcare, received the Frost & Sullivan Middle East Integrated Healthcare Company of the Year Award in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfinance.com/infrastructure-investment/nmc-guides-the-way-for-the-uaes-healthcare-sector|title=NMC guides the way for the UAE's healthcare sector|publisher=World Finance|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170430214825/http://www.worldfinance.com/infrastructure-investment/nmc-guides-the-way-for-the-uaes-healthcare-sector|archive-date=30 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> That same year, MILAAP honored Shetty with a Lifetime Achievement Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nmctrading.com/dr-b-r-shetty-receives-lifetime-achievement-award-3/|title=Dr. B.R. Shetty receives Lifetime Achievement Award|publisher=NMC Trading|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424174031/http://www.nmctrading.com/dr-b-r-shetty-receives-lifetime-achievement-award-3/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nAt the 2015 Gulf Business Industry Awards, Shetty was recognized as the Healthcare Business Leader of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gulfbusiness.com/gulf-business-industry-awards-2015-business-leaders-year/|title=Gulf Business Industry Awards 2015: Business Leaders of the Year|date=9 September 2015|publisher=Gulf Business|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424173736/http://gulfbusiness.com/gulf-business-industry-awards-2015-business-leaders-year/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> In November 2015, he was felicitated by More Ignatius Jacobite Syrian Orthodox Cathedral in Dubai.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brshetty.com/awards/dr-b-r-shetty-felicitated-by-mor-ignatius-jacobite-syrian-orthodox-cathedral/|title=Dr. B.R.Setty Felicitated By Mor Ignatius Jacobite Syrian Orthodox Cathedral, Dubai|publisher=Dr. B. R. Shetty|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424175818/http://www.brshetty.com/awards/dr-b-r-shetty-felicitated-by-mor-ignatius-jacobite-syrian-orthodox-cathedral/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = dead}}</ref> Shetty's NMC Healthcare was recognized at the 6th Middle East Business Leaders Awards in 2015, where Shetty was given the Industry Excellence in Healthcare Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/mebla-honours-industry-leaders|title=Mebla honours industry leaders|work=khaleej Times|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085800/http://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/mebla-honours-industry-leaders|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Shetty received the Golden Peacock Lifetime Achievement Award for Business Leadership.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldenpeacockaward.com/past-winners/individual-leadership-awards.html|title=Roll of Honour|publisher=Golden Peacock Awards|access-date=24 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424173821/http://www.goldenpeacockaward.com/past-winners/individual-leadership-awards.html|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> Also in 2016, Shetty won the Business Excellence Award from the Indian Business & Professional Council.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nmchealth.com/news/dr-b-r-shetty-honoured-with-business-excellence-award/|title=Dr. B.R. Shetty honoured with Business Excellence Award|publisher=NMC Health|access-date=24 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085934/http://www.nmchealth.com/news/dr-b-r-shetty-honoured-with-business-excellence-award/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = dead}}</ref> Middlesex University in Dubai awarded Shetty an Honorary Doctorate in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mdx.ac.ae/about-us/honorary-doctorates|title=Middlesex Dubai Honorary Graduates|publisher=Middlesex University Dubai|access-date=24 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424174731/http://www.mdx.ac.ae/about-us/honorary-doctorates|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2017, Shetty was honored at the Annual Health Awards with a special award for his contribution to the region's healthcare industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://article.wn.com/view/2017/01/23/Dr_B_R_Shetty_honoured_at_the_Annual_Health_Awards_2017_NMC_/|title=Dr. B. R. Shetty honoured at the Annual Health Awards 2017 (NMC Health plc)|publisher=World News|access-date=24 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085508/https://article.wn.com/view/2017/01/23/Dr_B_R_Shetty_honoured_at_the_Annual_Health_Awards_2017_NMC_/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> The following month, Shetty received the Nadaprabhu Kempegowda International Award at the Kempegowda International Festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newskarnataka.com/nri/kempegowda-international-festival-lays-emphasis-on-uniting-okkaligas-under-roof|title=Kempegowda International Festival lays emphasis on uniting Okkaligas under roof|publisher=News Karnataka|access-date=24 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424174146/http://www.newskarnataka.com/nri/kempegowda-international-festival-lays-emphasis-on-uniting-okkaligas-under-roof|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018 Shetty was recognized by Forbes Middle East among the top Indian leaders in the Arab world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gulfnews.com/business/revealed-top-indian-business-leaders-in-arab-world-1.2218991|title=Revealed: Top Indian business leaders in Arab world|publisher=Gulf News Business|accessdate=25 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190527090500/https://gulfnews.com/business/revealed-top-indian-business-leaders-in-arab-world-1.2218991|archive-date=27 May 2019|url-status = live}}</ref> In September 2018 Shetty received the C3 Lifetime Achievement Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/c3-us-arab-healthcare--business-summit-and-title-sponsor-alitheia-holdings-honors-keynote-speaker-dr-br-shetty-with-lifetime-achievement-award-300714982.html|publisher=PR Newswire|accessdate=25 August 2019|title=C3 US-Arab Healthcare & Business Summit and Title Sponsor Alitheia Holdings Honors Keynote Speaker Dr. B.R. Shetty with Lifetime Achievement Award|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825020538/https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/c3-us-arab-healthcare--business-summit-and-title-sponsor-alitheia-holdings-honors-keynote-speaker-dr-br-shetty-with-lifetime-achievement-award-300714982.html|archive-date=25 August 2019|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.brshetty.com/ Official website]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shetty, B. R.}}\n[[Category:Indian philanthropists]]\n[[Category:Mangaloreans]]\n[[Category:Tulu people]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Padma Shri in trade and industry]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Udupi district]]\n[[Category:Indian billionaires]]\n[[Category:Indian emigrants to the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:1942 births]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Karnataka]]\n[[Category:Giving Pledgers]]\n[[Category:21st-century philanthropists]]\n[[Category:Indian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Former billionaires]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Bavaguthu Raghuram Shetty\n| image              = File:Dr BR Shetty Official Pic.jpg\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1942|08|01|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Udupi]], [[Madras Presidency]], [[British India]] (now [[Karnataka]], [[India]])\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| occupation         = \n| known_for          = Founder [[NMC Health]], [[UAE Exchange]], [[Finablr]]\n| website            = {{url|brshetty.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Bavaguthu Raghuram Shetty''' (born 1 August 1942) is an Indian-born former [[billionaire]] businessman, and the founder of a number of companies based in the United Arab Emirates. He is founder of [[Abu Dhabi]]-based [[NMC Health]],<ref name=national/> and [[UAE Exchange]].<ref name=\"Indian Rich List in full - ArabianBusiness.com\"/> He is also the founder and chairman of Neopharma and BRS Ventures.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://businessworld.in/article/-I-Want-To-Be-The-No-1-Healthcare-Provider-In-India-Over-The-Next-10-Years-/23-03-2018-144373/| title=I Want To Be The No. 1 Healthcare Provider in India Over The Next 10 Years| author=Paramita Chatterjee, Suman K Jha| date=23 March 2018| publisher=BusinessWorld| access-date=8 May 2018| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180509012947/http://businessworld.in/article/-I-Want-To-Be-The-No-1-Healthcare-Provider-In-India-Over-The-Next-10-Years-/23-03-2018-144373/| archive-date=9 May 2018|url-status = live}}</ref> He is founder and co-chairman of [[Finablr]]. In 2018, the UAE Exchange brand became part of the financial services holding company, Finablr.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.forbesmiddleeast.com/en/billionaire-b-r-shetty-launches-new-financial-firms-holding-company-finablr/| title=Billionaire B.R. Shetty Launches New Financial Firms Holding Company Finablr| author=Mary Sophia| date=24 April 2018| publisher=Forbes Middle East| access-date=24 August 2018| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180825073919/https://www.forbesmiddleeast.com/en/billionaire-b-r-shetty-launches-new-financial-firms-holding-company-finablr/| archive-date=25 August 2018|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nShetty's initial interest in 1975 was in hospitals and hospitality, and has since diversified into pharmaceuticals, financial services, retail, advertising and information technology.<ref name=\"Indian Rich List in full - ArabianBusiness.com\">{{cite web | url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/indian-rich-list-in-full-342165.html#.V3JIbLh9600 | title=Indian Rich List in full - ArabianBusiness.com | publisher=ArabianBusiness | accessdate=28 June 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160424235811/http://www.arabianbusiness.com/indian-rich-list-in-full-342165.html#.V3JIbLh9600 | archive-date=24 April 2016 |url-status = live}}</ref> He was included on the ''[[Forbes]]'' list of India's 100 Richest People in 2015 and was listed as the 42nd richest person in 2020.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/br-shetty/| title=#47 B.R. Shetty| work=Forbes| accessdate=14 April 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161228013207/http://www.forbes.com/profile/br-shetty/| archive-date=28 December 2016|url-status = live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/br-shetty/#6862cc8b6cc7| title=#42 B.R. Shetty| work=Forbes| accessdate=20 February 2020| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514112322/https://www.forbes.com/profile/br-shetty/#6862cc8b6cc7| archive-date=14 May 2019| url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThere are allegations of misappropriation by Shetty at his companies and was forced to resign from his director positions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/how-indian-billionaire-bavaguthu-raghuram-shetty-who-owned-2-floors-of-burj-khalifa-went-bust-2182896 | title=How Indian billionaire Bavaguthu Raghuram Shetty went bust}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arabianbusiness.com/healthcare/440371-billionaire-br-shetty-resigns-from-abu-dhabis-nmc-health | title=Billionaire BR Shetty resigns from Abu Dhabi's NMC Health}}</ref> On April 8, 2020, NMC Health went into Administration in UK due to the insolvency of the company due to alleged frauds committed by Shetty.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nmc-insolvency-proceedings-inevitable-hospital-143125949.html | title=NMC into Administration}}</ref>\nDue to sharp drop in the share prices and Shetty pledging the shares for debts that he had incurred, it is believed that his net worth has fallen to fraction of the earlier estimate of $3.5 billion.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gulfbusiness.com/uae-based-br-shettys-fortune-drops-1-5bn-since-muddy-waters-attack/ | title=\"BR Shetty's fortune drops by $1.5 Billion| date=26 January 2020}}</ref> Consequently, Forbes has dropped Shetty from its 2020 annual list of billionaires.\n\nShetty fled the UAE fearing legal procedure there by lender banks, including Dubai Islamic Bank and ADCB.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arabianbusiness.com/banking-finance/444829-nmc-health-goes-into-administration-after-succumbing-to-creditors|title=NMC Health goes into administration after succumbing to creditors|website=ArabianBusiness.com}}</ref> On 15 April 2020,  Abu Dhabi Commercial Bank filed criminal complaint against NMC Health with the Attorney General's Office of UAE.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-nmc-health-adcb-crime-idUSKCN21X1BY|title=ADCB files criminal complaint against individuals over NMC Health|date=2020-04-15|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-04-16|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/corporate/nmcs-br-shetty-5-others-face-fraud-forgery-charges|title=NMC's BR Shetty, 5 others face fraud, forgery charges|last=John|first=Issac|website=Khaleej Times|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nShetty was born in [[Kapu, Karnataka|Kapu]], [[Udupi]] to [[Tulu language|Tulu]] speaking parents Shambhu Shetty and Koosamma Shetty in the 1940s to an ethnic [[Tuluva]] family.<ref name = \"Mangalorean Tuluva\">{{cite web |url=http://www.mangaloretoday.com/gulfnews/Mangalorean-Tuluva-B-R-Shetty-buys-Travelex-for-1-billion.html |title=Mangalorean Tuluva B R Shetty Buy's Travelex for 1 billion |date=14 June 2015 |accessdate=12 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802204342/http://www.mangaloretoday.com/gulfnews/Mangalorean-Tuluva-B-R-Shetty-buys-Travelex-for-1-billion.html |archive-date=2 August 2017 |url-status = live}}</ref> Shetty completed his pharmaceutical education in [[India]] and also served as the Vice-Chairman of the Municipal Council in Udupi. He married Chandrakumari Shetty and has four children.<ref name=\"Journey - Dr. B. R. Shetty\">{{cite web | url=http://www.brshetty.com/journey/ | title=Journey \u2013 Dr. B. R. Shetty | accessdate=28 June 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160614205457/http://www.brshetty.com/journey/ | archive-date=14 June 2016 |url-status = live}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nShetty immigrated to the UAE in 1973. After working as the country's first medical representative,<ref name=national/> he founded [[NMC Health|New Medical Centre Health]] (NMC) in 1975 to fill the need for personalized, cost-effective healthcare accessible to all.<ref name=national/><ref name=namma>{{cite web| url=http://namma.tv/dr-b-r-shetty-to-build-abu-dhabis-first-medical-university-in-honour-of-sheikh-zayed/| title=Dr B.R.Shetty to build Abu Dhabi's first medical university in honour of Sheikh Zayed| date=24 June 2016| publisher=NamMa TV| accessdate=2 May 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802174516/http://namma.tv/dr-b-r-shetty-to-build-abu-dhabis-first-medical-university-in-honour-of-sheikh-zayed/| archive-date=2 August 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> At that time, his wife was the only doctor in the clinic.<ref name=emi/> NMC is now the largest private healthcare provider in the UAE with over four million patients annually across 45 facilities spread over 12 cities and 8 countries, including UAE, KSA, Oman, Spain, Italy, Denmark, Colombia and Brazil. It is the first healthcare company from the GCC and the first company from Abu Dhabi to be listed on the premium segment of the [[London Stock Exchange]] and is part of the coveted [[FTSE 100 Index]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2017/09/02/gulf-private-hospitals-group-nmc-eyes-uk-launch-leap-ftse-100/|title=Gulf private hospitals group NMC eyes UK launch after leap into FTSE 100|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=2 September 2017|access-date=24 September 2017|first=Iain|last=Withers|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170913030605/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2017/09/02/gulf-private-hospitals-group-nmc-eyes-uk-launch-leap-ftse-100/|archive-date=13 September 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> Consequent to the request from the board of directors of NMC and on going investigation of potential financial irregularities, the company was de-listed from London Stock Exchange and was removed from FTSE 100 index. \n\nShetty established the [[UAE Exchange]] in 1980 in an attempt to ease the process of sending money by the expats to their families in their respective home countries. By 2016, it had expanded into over 31 countries and had approximately 800 direct offices. In 2014, it did over US$50 billion collectively in money remittance and exchange volumes.<ref name=emi>{{cite web| url=http://www.emirates247.com/news/emirates/dubai-dreams-from-jobless-medical-rep-to-billions-br-shetty-2016-08-10-1.638590| title=Dubai Dreams: From jobless medical rep to billions - BR Shetty| author=VM Sathish| date=10 August 2016| publisher=Emirates 24/7| accessdate=2 May 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170606205018/http://www.emirates247.com/news/emirates/dubai-dreams-from-jobless-medical-rep-to-billions-br-shetty-2016-08-10-1.638590| archive-date=6 June 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> Shetty acquired [[Travelex]], a major foreign exchange company, in 2014.<ref name=national>{{cite web| url=http://www.thenational.ae/business/industry-insights/economics/br-shetty-the-astute-businessman-who-turned-8-into-1bn#full| title=BR Shetty, the astute businessman who turned $8 into $1bn| author=Frank Kane| date=1 July 2014| publisher=The National| accessdate=2 May 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170428185222/http://www.thenational.ae/business/industry-insights/economics/br-shetty-the-astute-businessman-who-turned-8-into-1bn#full| archive-date=28 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref><ref name=khal/> Travelex has a global footprint including 1500 stores and 1300 ATMs across 27 countries. \n\nIn 2003, Shetty founded NMC Neopharma, a UAE based pharmaceutical manufacturer.<ref name=emi/> Inaugurated by the then President of India, [[A. P. J. Abdul Kalam]] in Abu Dhabi, Neopharma is centered on using the concept of modular manufacturing following global benchmarks in manufacturing technology and putting in place efficient control mechanisms. Neopharma has a research and development wing and works to provide quality medicines at affordable prices. The company also contracts manufacturing for international pharmaceutical companies as well as generic brands for companies including, but not limited to, [[Merck Group|Merck]], [[Pfizer]], [[AstraZeneca]], and [[Boots UK]].<ref name=emi/>\n\nIn 2012, Shetty led NMC through an [[initial public offering|IPO]] on the [[London Stock Exchange]], which raised $330 million. The funds went towards building a specialty hospital in [[Khalifa City]], Abu Dhabi.<ref name=gulfnews>{{cite web| url=http://gulfnews.com/business/sectors/general/dr-b-r-shetty-to-expand-his-nmc-group-in-uae-and-gcc-1.1400467| title=Dr B.R. Shetty to expand his NMC group in UAE and GCC| author=Fareed Rahman| date=18 October 2014| publisher=Gulf News| accessdate=2 May 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161006162305/http://gulfnews.com/business/sectors/general/dr-b-r-shetty-to-expand-his-nmc-group-in-uae-and-gcc-1.1400467| archive-date=6 October 2016|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2016, Shetty announced that he was building the first medical university in Abu Dhabi in honor of [[Zayed bin Sultan Al Nahyan|Sheikh Zayed]].<ref name=namma/> That same month, he was elected to be chairman of the Indian Business/Professional Group.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.bfirst.in/news/diaspora/8815/br-shetty-wants-promote-india-uae-ties-through-ibpg| title=BR Shetty wants to promote India-UAE ties through IBPG| date=7 June 2016| publisher=Bfirst| accessdate=2 May 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925083522/http://www.bfirst.in/news/diaspora/8815/br-shetty-wants-promote-india-uae-ties-through-ibpg| archive-date=25 September 2017| url-status=dead}}</ref> In August 2016, Shetty announced that he was building a 400-bed super-specialty hospital in Udupi in Karnataka through B R S Ventures.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.mangalorean.com/dr-br-shetty-build-400-bed-super-speciality-hospital-udupi/| title=Dr BR Shetty to Build 400-bed Super-specialty hospital in Udupi| date=25 August 2016| publisher=Mangalorean| accessdate=2 May 2017| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925132051/https://www.mangalorean.com/dr-br-shetty-build-400-bed-super-speciality-hospital-udupi/| archive-date=25 September 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> Shetty also owned a hospital in [[Alexandria]], two hospitals in Nepal, and acquired a hospital in Cairo as part of his personal portfolio under the same company.<ref name=gulfnews/>\n\nIn August 2019, BRS Ventures announced plans to invest $5 billion in developing healthcare facilities across India.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.businesstoday.in/current/corporate/jang-sangh-hand-billionaire-b-r-shetty-5-billion-dollar-investments-in-indian-healthcare/story/373353.html | title=Old Jan Sangh hand, billionaire B R Shetty plans $5 billion investment in Indian healthcare | publisher=Business Today | accessdate=25 August 2019 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825084836/https://www.businesstoday.in/current/corporate/jang-sangh-hand-billionaire-b-r-shetty-5-billion-dollar-investments-in-indian-healthcare/story/373353.html | archive-date=25 August 2019 |url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2020, [[Bloomberg News]] report casted doubts on his real holding amidst the short-selling of NMC Health by [[Muddy Waters Research]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/business/a-jet-setting-billionaire-had-it-all-then-carson-block-came-along/articleshow/74204580.cms|title=Jet-setting billionaire Bavaguthu Raghuram Shetty had it all. Then Carson Block came along| publisher=Bloomberg| accessdate= 20 February 2020}}</ref> Also in February 2020, Shetty was ousted from the NMC Health board following a corporate governance scandal over his holdings in the company.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Correspondent|first=Ben Martin, Senior City|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/nmcs-founder-forced-out-over-shares-scandal-cr59jz2s6|title=NMC's founder forced out over shares scandal|access-date=2020-02-25|language=en|issn=0140-0460}}</ref>\n\nOn April 8, 2020, NMC went into Administration in UK due to the insolvency of the company due to alleged frauds committed by Shetty.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nmc-insolvency-proceedings-inevitable-hospital-143125949.html|title=NMC Heads to Administration After Giving In to Creditor Demands|website=finance.yahoo.com}}</ref>\n\n==Other activities==\nShetty has invested in a medical institution in the north Indian state of Uttarakhand. He is the founder and patron of the Indian Pharmaceutical Association in the Emirates, and is a member of the Advisory Board (Financial Sector), Economic Department, Government of Dubai, UAE and the Pharmaceutical Committee, Dubai. He is also the chairman of [[Abu Dhabi Indian School]] and Bright Riders School.<ref name=\"Indian tycoons storm Arabian Business Expat Power List 2011 - ArabianBusiness.com\">{{cite web | url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/indian-tycoons-storm-arabian-business-expat-power-list-2011-383132.html#.V3JKfbh9600 | title=Indian tycoons storm Arabian Business Expat Power List 2011 - ArabianBusiness.com | publisher=ArabianBusiness | accessdate=28 June 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815070908/http://www.arabianbusiness.com/indian-tycoons-storm-arabian-business-expat-power-list-2011-383132.html#.V3JKfbh9600 | archive-date=15 August 2016 |url-status = live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://brightriders.ae/?page_id=176|title=Chairman's Message {{!}} Bright Riders School, Abu Dhabi|website=brightriders.ae|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802164450/http://brightriders.ae/?page_id=176|archive-date=2 August 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2015, Shetty was elected as the Chairman to the board of directors of UAE Exchange.<ref name=khal>{{cite web|url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/dr-br-shetty-takes-over-as-chairman-of-uae-exchange|title=Dr B.R. Shetty takes over as chairman of UAE Exchange|work=Khaleej Times|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085905/http://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/dr-br-shetty-takes-over-as-chairman-of-uae-exchange|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/uae-exchange-appoints-b-r-shetty-as-chairman-promoth-manghat-as-ceo/articleshow/48652739.cms|title=UAE Exchange appoints B R Shetty as Chairman, Promoth Manghat as CEO|newspaper=The Economic Times|date=24 August 2015|publisher=Economic Times India|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424090633/http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/uae-exchange-appoints-b-r-shetty-as-chairman-promoth-manghat-as-ceo/articleshow/48652739.cms|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> He was named chairman of The Indian Business/Professional Group in June 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newskarnataka.com/nri/dr-b-r-shetty-to-head-the-indian-businessprofessional-group|title=Dr B R Shetty to head The Indian Business/Professional Group|publisher=News Karnataka|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085646/http://www.newskarnataka.com/nri/dr-b-r-shetty-to-head-the-indian-businessprofessional-group|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> H. H. Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid al Maktoum nominated Shetty as a member of the UAE medical council in September 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.bfirst.in/news/2016_09_09/12860|title=Businessman BR Shetty nominated to medical council by PM of Dubai|publisher=Bfirst}}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, Shetty announced that he would invest Rs 1000 crore ($157.3 million) to produce a film with director [[V. A. Shrikumar Menon]]. The film, starring [[Mohanlal]], was to be based on the novel [[Randamoozham]], a retelling of [[Mahabharata]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Billionaire B. R. Shetty aims for $1 billion in revenue from Indian film epic|url=https://in.reuters.com/article/nmc-health-shetty-film/billionaire-b-r-shetty-aims-for-1-billion-in-revenue-from-indian-film-epic-idINKBN18V0SR|access-date=28 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171027181423/https://in.reuters.com/article/nmc-health-shetty-film/billionaire-b-r-shetty-aims-for-1-billion-in-revenue-from-indian-film-epic-idINKBN18V0SR|archive-date=27 October 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\nIn May 2019, however, the film was shelved due to creative issues.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mohanlal's Rs 1000 crore film project 'Randamoozham' shelved|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2019/apr/03/mohanlals-rs-1000-crore-film-project-randamoozham-shelved-1959795.html|access-date=20 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190805223955/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2019/apr/03/mohanlals-rs-1000-crore-film-project-randamoozham-shelved-1959795.html|archive-date=5 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and recognition ==\n{{Overly detailed|Section|date=February 2020}}\nIn 2005, Shetty was awarded the highest civilian distinction in the Emirate, the [[Abu Dhabi Awards]].<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.thenational.ae/uae/abu-dhabi-awards-b-r-shetty-1.119120 | title = Abu Dhabi Awards: B R Shetty | date = 23 May 2015 | work = The National | access-date = 23 September 2019 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190923071607/https://www.thenational.ae/uae/abu-dhabi-awards-b-r-shetty-1.119120 | archive-date = 23 September 2019 | url-status = live }}</ref> Given by H. H. Sheikh [[Mohammed bin Zayed Al Nahyan]], the Crown Prince of Abu Dhabi, the first year the distinction was awarded.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenational.ae/uae/abu-dhabi-awards-b-r-shetty|title=Abu Dhabi Awards: B R Shetty|publisher=The National|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170422235344/http://www.thenational.ae/uae/abu-dhabi-awards-b-r-shetty|archive-date=22 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> Also in 2005, U.S. India Friendship Society presented Shetty the Distinguished Entrepreneur Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neopharmauae.com/en/news.asp?News_Id=173-Dr.-B.R.-Shetty-received-The-Distinguished-Entrepreneur-Award-from-the-US-India-Friendship-Society-|title=Dr. B.R. Shetty received The Distinguished Entrepreneur Award from the US India Friendship Society|publisher=Neopharma|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424173745/http://www.neopharmauae.com/en/news.asp?News_Id=173-Dr.-B.R.-Shetty-received-The-Distinguished-Entrepreneur-Award-from-the-US-India-Friendship-Society-|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = dead}}</ref>\n\nShetty was honoured by the [[Pravasi Bharatiya Samman]] in 2007.<ref name=\"The recipients of Pravasi Bharatiya Samman - Times of India\">{{cite web | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/The-recipients-of-Pravasi-Bharatiya-Samman/articleshow/1113368.cms | title=The recipients of Pravasi Bharatiya Samman \u2013 Times of India | work=Times of India| accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"New Delhi B R Shetty Among Padma Shree Awardees\">{{cite web | url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/news_disp.asp?n_id=56080 | title=New Delhi B R Shetty Among Padma Shree Awardees | publisher=Daijiworld Media Pvt Ltd Mangalore | accessdate=28 June 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303170744/http://www.daijiworld.com/news/news_disp.asp?n_id=56080 | archive-date=3 March 2016 |url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nErnst & Young Middle East honored Shetty with the Entrepreneur of the year finalist award in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.emirates247.com/eb247/companies-markets/five-uae-execs-in-running-for-ernst-young-award-2008-01-17-1.216304|title=Five UAE execs in running for Ernst & Young award|publisher=Emirates 24/7|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085817/http://www.emirates247.com/eb247/companies-markets/five-uae-execs-in-running-for-ernst-young-award-2008-01-17-1.216304|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nShetty received the [[Padma Shri|Padmashree]] awarded by the [[President of India]] in 2009 for his contribution in the field of trade and industry.<ref name=\"IBPC Felicitates Padma Shri Award Winners - Khaleej Times\">{{cite web | url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/ibpc-felicitates-padma-shri-award-winners | title=IBPC Felicitates Padma Shri Award Winners \u2013 Khaleej Times | work=Khaleej Times| accessdate=28 June 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160808123305/http://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/ibpc-felicitates-padma-shri-award-winners | archive-date=8 August 2016 |url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2011, he received the Asian Achievers Award from the Human Achievers Foundation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/article/20110713/ARTICLE/307139999/1002|title=Asian Achievers Awards for Dhahi Khalfan, others|work=Khaleej Times|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424174100/http://www.khaleejtimes.com/article/20110713/ARTICLE/307139999/1002|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2012, Pharma Leaders founded by Satya Brahma declared Shetty as Global Indian of the Year along with [[Kiran Mazumdar-Shaw|Kiran Mazumdar Shaw]] at 5th Annual Pharmaceutical Leadership Summit & Pharma Leaders Business Leadership Awards 2012 in Mumbai.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pharmaleaders.tv/biocon-chief-dr-kiran-majumdar-shaw-nmc-chief-dr-b-r-shetty-declared-global-indian-of-the-year-2/|title=Biocon Chief Dr. Kiran Majumdar Shaw & NMC Chief Dr B.R.Shetty Declared Global Indian of the Year {{!}} Pharmaleaders TV|website=pharmaleaders.tv|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171024205347/http://pharmaleaders.tv/biocon-chief-dr-kiran-majumdar-shaw-nmc-chief-dr-b-r-shetty-declared-global-indian-of-the-year-2/|archive-date=24 October 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, Shetty was recognized as one of Asia's most promising leaders at the Asian Brand & Leadership Summit.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=189157|title=UAE Exchange named leader, most promising brand in Asia|publisher=Daiji World|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085721/http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=189157|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> In March 2013, he was awarded the International Achievers Summit's Lifetime Achievement Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nmctrading.com/dr-b-r-shetty-receives-lifetime-achievement-award/|title=Dr. B.R. Shetty receives Lifetime Achievement Award|publisher=NMC Trading|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424174516/http://www.nmctrading.com/dr-b-r-shetty-receives-lifetime-achievement-award/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> That same year, Shetty received the Asian Business Leadership Forum India-UAE Business Icons Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ablfawards.com/2013-winners/|title=ABLF Awards 2013 Winners|publisher=ABLF|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161211033716/http://www.ablfawards.com/2013-winners/|archive-date=11 December 2016|url-status = dead}}</ref> He also received the 2013 Frost & Sullivan Lifetime Achievement Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.frost.com/prod/servlet/press-release.pag?docid=291322634|title=Dr. B R Shetty honoured with Frost & Sullivan - Lifetime Achievement Award for the Year 2013|publisher=Frost & Sullivan|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170425031103/https://www.frost.com/prod/servlet/press-release.pag?docid=291322634|archive-date=25 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Forbes Middle East recognized Shetty with the Top Indian Leaders in the UAE Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbesmiddleeast.com/forbes-middle-east-unveils-top-indian-leaders-in-the-arab-region|title=Forbes Middle East Reveals Top Indian Leaders in the Arab World|website=Forbes Middle East|publisher=Forbes|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> He also received the Lakshya Business Visionary Award in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/getahead/report/achievers-from-salesman-to-biz-tycoon-a-serial-entrepreneurs-success-mantras/20141105.htm|title=From salesman to biz tycoon: A serial entrepreneur's success mantras|publisher=Rediff|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424173734/http://www.rediff.com/getahead/report/achievers-from-salesman-to-biz-tycoon-a-serial-entrepreneurs-success-mantras/20141105.htm|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> That same year, Shetty was recognized with the International Achievement Award at the Indian Innovator Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/entmagazineme/docs/entrepreneur_middle_east_january_20|title=Indian Innovator Awards 2014|publisher=Entrepreneur Middle East|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424173725/https://issuu.com/entmagazineme/docs/entrepreneur_middle_east_january_20|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2015, the Indian Club - Bahrain recognized Shetty with a Centenary Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=295424|title=Bahrain : Dr Kalam presents Indian Club Centenary awards to Colaco, B R Shetty|publisher=Daiji World|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085429/http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=295424|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> He received the Deal of the Year Award at the 2015 Indian CEO Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/sunil-vaswani-takes-top-honours-at-indian-ceo-awards-582410.html|title=Sunil Vaswani takes top honours at Indian CEO Awards|publisher=Arabian Business|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008135040/http://www.arabianbusiness.com/sunil-vaswani-takes-top-honours-at-indian-ceo-awards-582410.html|archive-date=8 October 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> In June 2015, Shetty received the Business Personality of the Year award from Crowe Horwath International.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nmchealth.com/dr-b-r-shetty-has-received-the-prestigious-business-personality-of-the-year-award/|title=Dr. B.R. Shetty has received the prestigious Business Personality of the Year award|publisher=NMV Health|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150805020024/http://www.nmchealth.com/dr-b-r-shetty-has-received-the-prestigious-business-personality-of-the-year-award/|archive-date=5 August 2015|url-status = dead}}</ref> That same month, Shetty received the Arabian Indian Czars award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2015-06-18/news/63567767_1_fadnavis-sunil-vaswani-rizwan-sajan|title=Arabian Indian Czars Award: Times Now felicitates successful Indians in Middle East|work=The Economic Times|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151018060431/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2015-06-18/news/63567767_1_fadnavis-sunil-vaswani-rizwan-sajan|archive-date=18 October 2015|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nShetty received the Global Indian Achiever Award in 2015 from H. H. Sheikh Nahyan Bin Mubarak al Nahyan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nmchealth.com/dr-b-r-shetty-honoured-global-indian-achiever-award/|title=Dr. B R Shetty honoured with Global Indian Achiever Award|publisher=NMC Health|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171031042109/http://www.nmchealth.com/dr-b-r-shetty-honoured-global-indian-achiever-award/|archive-date=31 October 2017|url-status = dead}}</ref> Also in 2015, H. H. Prince Faisal Bin Saud Bin Musaed Bin Abdulaziz presented Shetty with the National Cultural Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sauress.com/en/saudigazette/240107|title=Indian tycoon Shetty is honored with National Cultural Award|work=The Saudi Gazette|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424173839/http://www.sauress.com/en/saudigazette/240107|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> Shetty's company, NMC Healthcare, received the Frost & Sullivan Middle East Integrated Healthcare Company of the Year Award in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfinance.com/infrastructure-investment/nmc-guides-the-way-for-the-uaes-healthcare-sector|title=NMC guides the way for the UAE's healthcare sector|publisher=World Finance|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170430214825/http://www.worldfinance.com/infrastructure-investment/nmc-guides-the-way-for-the-uaes-healthcare-sector|archive-date=30 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> That same year, MILAAP honored Shetty with a Lifetime Achievement Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nmctrading.com/dr-b-r-shetty-receives-lifetime-achievement-award-3/|title=Dr. B.R. Shetty receives Lifetime Achievement Award|publisher=NMC Trading|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424174031/http://www.nmctrading.com/dr-b-r-shetty-receives-lifetime-achievement-award-3/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nAt the 2015 Gulf Business Industry Awards, Shetty was recognized as the Healthcare Business Leader of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gulfbusiness.com/gulf-business-industry-awards-2015-business-leaders-year/|title=Gulf Business Industry Awards 2015: Business Leaders of the Year|date=9 September 2015|publisher=Gulf Business|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424173736/http://gulfbusiness.com/gulf-business-industry-awards-2015-business-leaders-year/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> In November 2015, he was felicitated by More Ignatius Jacobite Syrian Orthodox Cathedral in Dubai.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brshetty.com/awards/dr-b-r-shetty-felicitated-by-mor-ignatius-jacobite-syrian-orthodox-cathedral/|title=Dr. B.R.Setty Felicitated By Mor Ignatius Jacobite Syrian Orthodox Cathedral, Dubai|publisher=Dr. B. R. Shetty|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424175818/http://www.brshetty.com/awards/dr-b-r-shetty-felicitated-by-mor-ignatius-jacobite-syrian-orthodox-cathedral/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = dead}}</ref> Shetty's NMC Healthcare was recognized at the 6th Middle East Business Leaders Awards in 2015, where Shetty was given the Industry Excellence in Healthcare Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/mebla-honours-industry-leaders|title=Mebla honours industry leaders|work=khaleej Times|access-date=23 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085800/http://www.khaleejtimes.com/business/local/mebla-honours-industry-leaders|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Shetty received the Golden Peacock Lifetime Achievement Award for Business Leadership.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldenpeacockaward.com/past-winners/individual-leadership-awards.html|title=Roll of Honour|publisher=Golden Peacock Awards|access-date=24 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424173821/http://www.goldenpeacockaward.com/past-winners/individual-leadership-awards.html|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> Also in 2016, Shetty won the Business Excellence Award from the Indian Business & Professional Council.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nmchealth.com/news/dr-b-r-shetty-honoured-with-business-excellence-award/|title=Dr. B.R. Shetty honoured with Business Excellence Award|publisher=NMC Health|access-date=24 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085934/http://www.nmchealth.com/news/dr-b-r-shetty-honoured-with-business-excellence-award/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = dead}}</ref> Middlesex University in Dubai awarded Shetty an Honorary Doctorate in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mdx.ac.ae/about-us/honorary-doctorates|title=Middlesex Dubai Honorary Graduates|publisher=Middlesex University Dubai|access-date=24 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424174731/http://www.mdx.ac.ae/about-us/honorary-doctorates|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2017, Shetty was honored at the Annual Health Awards with a special award for his contribution to the region's healthcare industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://article.wn.com/view/2017/01/23/Dr_B_R_Shetty_honoured_at_the_Annual_Health_Awards_2017_NMC_/|title=Dr. B. R. Shetty honoured at the Annual Health Awards 2017 (NMC Health plc)|publisher=World News|access-date=24 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085508/https://article.wn.com/view/2017/01/23/Dr_B_R_Shetty_honoured_at_the_Annual_Health_Awards_2017_NMC_/|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref> The following month, Shetty received the Nadaprabhu Kempegowda International Award at the Kempegowda International Festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newskarnataka.com/nri/kempegowda-international-festival-lays-emphasis-on-uniting-okkaligas-under-roof|title=Kempegowda International Festival lays emphasis on uniting Okkaligas under roof|publisher=News Karnataka|access-date=24 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424174146/http://www.newskarnataka.com/nri/kempegowda-international-festival-lays-emphasis-on-uniting-okkaligas-under-roof|archive-date=24 April 2017|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018 Shetty was recognized by Forbes Middle East among the top Indian leaders in the Arab world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gulfnews.com/business/revealed-top-indian-business-leaders-in-arab-world-1.2218991|title=Revealed: Top Indian business leaders in Arab world|publisher=Gulf News Business|accessdate=25 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190527090500/https://gulfnews.com/business/revealed-top-indian-business-leaders-in-arab-world-1.2218991|archive-date=27 May 2019|url-status = live}}</ref> In September 2018 Shetty received the C3 Lifetime Achievement Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/c3-us-arab-healthcare--business-summit-and-title-sponsor-alitheia-holdings-honors-keynote-speaker-dr-br-shetty-with-lifetime-achievement-award-300714982.html|publisher=PR Newswire|accessdate=25 August 2019|title=C3 US-Arab Healthcare & Business Summit and Title Sponsor Alitheia Holdings Honors Keynote Speaker Dr. B.R. Shetty with Lifetime Achievement Award|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825020538/https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/c3-us-arab-healthcare--business-summit-and-title-sponsor-alitheia-holdings-honors-keynote-speaker-dr-br-shetty-with-lifetime-achievement-award-300714982.html|archive-date=25 August 2019|url-status = live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [