 date|2007|1|21}}\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 47\n| Title               = The Final Decisive Battle! The Legendary Prank King\n| TranslitTitle       = Iyoiyo Kessen! Densetsu no Itazura \u014c\n| NativeTitle         = \u3044\u3088\u3044\u3088\u3051\u3063\u305b\u3093!\u3067\u3093\u305b\u3064\u306e\u30a4\u30bf\u30ba\u30e9\u738b\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2007|1|28}}\n}}\n|}\n\n===Series 3=== \nIn July 2019, it was announced that a new television anime series of Kaiketsu Zorori would be released in early 2020.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chapman |first1=Paul |title=Clever Fox Returns in Spring of 2020 for New Kaiketsu Zorori TV Anime |url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2019/07/04/clever-fox-returns-in-spring-of-2020-for-new-kaiketsu-zorori-tv-anime |website=[[Crunchyroll]] |accessdate=July 4, 2019 |date=July 4, 2019}}</ref> The anime is the first television anime adaptation of the book series in 13 years since the second anime ended in 2007. In February 2020, it was announced to debut on April 5 on [[NHK Educational TV|NHK Educational]].<ref name=\"Zorori Series 3\">{{cite web |last1=Mateo |first1=Alex |title=New Kaiketsu Zorori Anime Reveals Cast, Theme Songs, April 5 Premiere |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-02-13/new-kaiketsu-zorori-anime-reveals-cast-theme-songs-april-5-premiere/.156416 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=February 13, 2020 |date=February 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe series, titled ''Motto! Majime ni Fumajime Kaiketsu Zorori'', is a joint collaboration between [[Ajia-do Animation Works|Ajia-do]] and [[Bandai Namco Pictures]].<ref name=\"Zorori Series 3\"/> Takahide Ogata serves as director, Atsuhiro Tomioka in charge of the series' composition, Hideyuki Funakoshi as character designer, and K\u014dhei Tanaka as the composer.<ref name=\"Zorori Series 3\"/> [[K\u014dichi Yamadera]] performs the opening theme song \"Motto! Motto! Kaiketsu Zorori\" as Zorori, and ONEPIXCEL is performing the ending theme \"Shalalala.\"<ref name=\"Zorori Series 3\"/>\n\nYamadera, [[Rikako Aikawa]], and [[Motoko Kumai]] reprised their respective roles.<ref name=\"Zorori Series 3\"/> This series marks the debut of Zorori's rival, Beat (voiced by [[Y\u016bki Kaji]]).<ref name=\"Zorori Series 3\"/>\n{|class=\"wikitable\" width=\"99%\"\n|-\n! # !! Title !! Original air date\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" bgcolor=\"#800080\"|\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 01\n| Title               = A Bride and Zorori's Castle\n| TranslitTitle       = Hanayome to Zororij\u014d\n| NativeTitle         = \u306f\u306a\u3088\u3081\u3068\u30be\u30ed\u30ea\u3058\u3087\u3046\n| NativeTitleLangCode = \n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|4|5}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n| LineColor           = 800080\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 02\n| Title               = Zorori vs. Hot Blood Beat\n| TranslitTitle       = Zorori VS Nekketsu no Beat\n| NativeTitle         = \u30be\u30ed\u30eaVS\u306d\u3063\u3051\u3064\u306e\u30d3\u30fc\u30c8\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|4|12}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n| LineColor           = 800080\n}} \n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 03\n| Title               = Curry vs. Author Riyoku\n| TranslitTitle       = Curry VS Chono no Riyoku\n| NativeTitle         = \u30ab\u30ec\u30fcVS\u3061\u3087\u3046\u306e\u3046\u308a\u3087\u304f\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|4|19}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n| LineColor           = 800080\n}} <!--\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 04\n| Title               = \n| TranslitTitle       = \n| NativeTitle         = \n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|4|26}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n| LineColor           = 800080\n}} -->\n|}\n\n==Movies==\n\n===Tokyo Movie Shinsha===\n{{nihongo|'''Kaiketsu Zorori: I am a Wizard/Treasure Hunt'''|\u304b\u3044\u3051\u3064\u30be\u30ed\u30ea:\u307e\u307b\u3046\u4f7f\u3044\u306e\u3067\u3057/\u5927\u304b\u3044\u305e\u304f\u306e\u5b9d\u3055\u304c\u3057|''Kaiketsu Zorori: Mahou Tsukai no Deshi/Dai Kaizoku no Takara Sagashi''}} \n:Released in 1993, this movie adapts books 3 and 4. It was shown alongside {{nihongo|''[[Anpanman#Movies|Soreike! Anpanman: Nosshi the Dinosaur's Big Adventure]]''|\u305d\u308c\u3044\u3051!\u30a2\u30f3\u30d1\u30f3\u30de\u30f3 \u6050\u7adc\u30ce\u30c3\u30b7\u30fc\u306e\u5927\u5192\u967a|Soreike Anpanman Kyouryuu Nosshii no Daibouken}}.\n\n===Ajia-do Animation Works===\n{{nihongo|'''Quest for the Mysterious Treasure'''|\u306a\u305e\u306e\u304a\u5b9d\u5927\u3055\u304f\u305b\u3093|''Nazo no Otakara Daisakusen''}} \n:This movie adapts books 38 and 39. It was shown alongside [[Keroro Guns\u014d the Super Movie]] on March 1, 2006. Zorori, Ishishi, and Noshishi help out Tail find a treasure her father Gale died trying to figure out. Along the way, they are helped out by Youkai-sensei and several monsters, but Tiger and his crew stand in their way.\n\n{{nihongo|'''G-G-G-Great Adventure'''|\u3060\u30fb\u3060\u30fb\u3060\u30fb\u3060\u3044\u307c\u3046\u3051\u3093!|''Da-Da-Da-Daibouken!''}} \n:Based on books 47 and 48. Zorori, Ishishi, and Noshishi, while out searching for treasure, come upon a town with a widespread illness. In order to make the secret medicine for it, they must set out on an adventure. This will be the first full-length Zorori movie.\n\n{{nihongo|'''Will Protect It! The Dinosaur Egg'''|\u307e\u3082\u308b\u305c! \u304d\u3087\u3046\u308a\u3085\u3046\u306e\u305f\u307e\u3054|''Mamoru ze! Kyouryuu no Tamago''}} \n:Based on book 40. Zorori with his friends Ishishi and Noshishi get an invitation from their friend, a mother dinosaur, to come see a dinosaur egg that will hatch soon. The group receives a warm welcome when they arrive at the legendary dinosaur island. However, a huge typhoon hits the island and the egg goes missing. Zorori goes on a quest to save the egg and return it safely to its family.\n\n{{nihongo|'''The Space Heroes'''|\u3046\u3061\u3085\u3046\u306e\u52c7\u8005\u305f\u3061|''Uch\u016b no Y\u016bsha-tachi''}} \n:Zorori, Ishishi, and Noshishi search for a meteor that sunk in the ocean. When under attack by octopi, Zorori accidentally launches his submarine into space and land on another planet. \n\n{{nihongo|'''The Secret of Double Z'''|ZZ\u306e\u3072\u307f\u3064|''ZZ no Himitsu''}} \n:Zorori, Ishishi, and Noshishi travel back in time and meet a younger Zororene.\n\n==Manga==\nComic Bombom published 10 volumes of a manga series starring Kaiketsu Zorori. It was written by Yutaka Hara and illustrated by Kimura Hiroki. \n\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n | OneLanguage = yes\n | WithTitle   = yes\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 01\n | RelDate         = September 2004 \n | ISBN            = 978-4-591-08264-5 \n | Title           = {{nihongo|\"Kaiketsu Zorori and Urashima Taro\"|\u304b\u3044\u3051\u3064\u30be\u30ed\u30ea\u306e\u3046\u3089\u3057\u307e\u592a\u90ce|\"Kaiketsu Zorori n\u014drashi ma Tar\u014d\"}}\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 02\n | RelDate         = March 2005 \n | ISBN            = 978-4-591-08557-8 \n | Title           = {{nihongo|\"Kaiketsu Zorori and Momotaro\"|\u304b\u3044\u3051\u3064\u30be\u30ed\u30ea\u306e\u3082\u3082\u592a\u90ce|\"Kaiketsu Zorori no momo Tar\u014d\"}}\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 03\n | RelDate         = September 2005 \n | ISBN            = 4-591-08644-5 \n | Title           = {{nihongo|\"Kaiketsu Zorori and Snow White\"|\u304b\u3044\u3051\u3064\u30be\u30ed\u30ea\u306e\u767d\u96ea\u59eb|\"Kaiketsu Zorori no shirayukihime\"}}\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 04\n | RelDate         = March 2006 \n | ISBN            = 978-4-591-09010-7 \n | Title           = {{nihongo|\"Kaiketsu Zorori and Princess Kaguya\"|\u304b\u3044\u3051\u3064\u30be\u30ed\u30ea\u306e\u304b\u3050\u3084\u59eb|\"Kaiketsu Zorori no kaguyahime\"}}\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 05\n | RelDate         = September 2006 \n | ISBN            = 978-4-591-09430-3 \n | Title           = {{nihongo|\"Kaiketsu Zorori and Little Red Riding Hood\"|\u304b\u3044\u3051\u3064\u30be\u30ed\u30ea\u306e\u8d64\u305a\u304d\u3093|\"Kaiketsu Zorori no akazukin\"}}\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 06\n | RelDate         = March 2007\n | ISBN            = 978-4-591-09738-0\n | Title           = {{nihongo|\"Kaiketsu Zorori's Rice Ball\"|\u304b\u3044\u3051\u3064\u30be\u30ed\u30ea\u306e\u304a\u3080\u3059\u3073\u3053\u308d\u308a\u3093|\"Kaiketsu Zorori no omusubi koro rin\"}}\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 07\n | RelDate         = December 2007\n | ISBN            = 978-4-591-10031-8 \n | Title           = {{nihongo|\"Kaiketsu Zorori the Naked King\"|\u304b\u3044\u3051\u3064\u30be\u30ed\u30ea\u306e\u306f\u3060\u304b\u306e\u738b\u3055\u307e|\"Kaiketsu Zorori no wada ka no \u014dsama\"}}\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 08\n | RelDate         = July 2008\n | ISBN            = 978-4-591-10421-7 \n | Title           = {{nihongo|\"Scarlet Zorori Aladdin and Magic Lamp\"|\u304b\u3044\u3051\u3064\u30be\u30ed\u30ea\u306e\u30a2\u30e9\u30b8\u30f3\u3068\u9b54\u6cd5\u306e\u30e9\u30f3\u30d7|\"Kaiketsu Zorori no arajintomah\u014dnoranpu\"}}\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 09\n | RelDate         = December 2008\n | ISBN            = 978-4-591-10625-9 \n | Title           = {{nihongo|\"Kaiketsu Zorori, Jack, and the Beanstalk\"|\u304b\u3044\u3051\u3064\u30be\u30ed\u30ea\u306e\u30b8\u30e3\u30c3\u30af\u3068\u8c46\u306e\u6728|\"Kaiketsu Zorori no jakkutomamenoki\"}}\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n | VolumeNumber    = 10\n | RelDate         = June 2009\n | ISBN            = 978-4-591-11027-0\n | Title           = {{nihongo|\"Kaiketsu Zorori and the Sleeping Princess of the Forest\"|\u304b\u3044\u3051\u3064\u30be\u30ed\u30ea\u306e\u7720\u308a\u306e\u68ee\u306e\u59eb|\"Kaiketsu Zorori no nemurinomori no hime\"}}\n}}\n